title: white velvet icing
directions: Mix flour and sugar and slowly stir in milk.
Stirring constantly, cook over low heat until mixture is very thick and has boiled about 1 minute.
Chill.
Cream butter and gradually add sugar and beat until mixture is very fluffy.
Slowly beat in cooled milk mixture and vanilla.
Spread on cake.

title: vera's chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup Italian salad dressing and mix lightly.
Could use Mozzarella cheese.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Mix spinach, soup mix, sour cream, and chestnuts--well!
Spread in 9x13 casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 325° approximately 30 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour 10 minutes.	Makes 2 loaves.

title: baked alaska
directions: Trim layer of sponge cake or layer cake 1-inch bigger on all sides than a brick of ice cream.
Place on a wooden cutting board. Make meringue:
Gradually add sugar to stiffly beaten egg whites and beat until meringue forms peaks.
Place brick of ice cream on cake.
Strip of paper under cake will help slide dessert onto plate.
Spread meringue over ice cream and cake.
Seal carefully to edges of cake.
Bake in very hot oven, 450°, until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
To serve, slice from board to plate. Serve quickly.

title: pesto
directions: Chop nuts in blender.
Blend in olive oil, basil, garlic and cheese.
To store, press into container and freeze, or cover with a thin layer of olive oil and keep refrigerated.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix milk and molasses.
Add dry ingredients and raisins.
Pour into well-greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours until bread tests done.
Cool in pan.

title: fried green beans
directions: Cook bacon, then crumble.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of bacon grease.
Add beans to bacon and reserved bacon grease.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir over high heat until steaming.
Cover and simmer over low heat 20 minutes.
Stir once or twice.

title: penuche
directions: Boil sugar and milk, stirring as needed to prevent curdling and scorching.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from fire. Add butter. Cool. Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts. Pour quickly into oiled pan.
Makes 10 to 12 (1-inch) squares.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown meat in salad oil.
Remove from pan and set aside.

title: it makes a great cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, and the rest as called for.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sister long's cobbler
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt stick of margarine.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk to make batter.
Pour into pan over butter.
Add fruit.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: toffee crackers
directions: Boil butter and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over saltine crackers (lined on a cookie sheet).
Put in oven for 5 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and pour chocolate chips over.
Let set, then spread with a knife.

title: sloppy mike's
directions: Fry beef (with onion to taste); drain the grease.
Put the beef back into the skillet.
Add soup.
Add the ketchup, mustard, barbecue and brown sugar.
Cover lightly with Tabasco and diced pepper.
Bring to a boil; let it cool a little.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Mix all this together.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve sauce over this.
Take 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1/3 cup milk, stirring to make smooth, then heat 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes in loaf pan.

title: quick italian salad
directions: Toss the first six ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Pour dressing over all and toss lightly to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: dolly's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion and bell pepper and cook until tender.
Add Prego and let simmer.
Cook noodles; drain. Mix eggs, cheese and cottage cheese.
Put layer of noodles, layer of sauce and layer of cheese.
Repeat, having cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: party sandwiches
directions: There are no exact measurements for this recipe.
Use amounts to your own preferences. Cut meat into very small cubes.
Add cream cheese that has been softened to room temperature.
Add green onions, salt and enough mayonnaise to make it into a spreading consistency.
Cut crusts from bread and make sandwiches with the spread.
Cut into shapes.
You may also use cookie cutters to make prettier sandwiches.

title: sausage balls
directions: All ingredients
should be at room temperature.
Mix by hand to blend well.
Form into small balls and bake 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.
Drain on paper towel.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2-quart dish.
Cook finely chopped cabbage in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes; drain and cool.
In mixing bowl, blend eggs, 1/2 butter, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir in cabbage.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Blend remaining butter with bread crumbs; sprinkle over cabbage.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put sugar and flour in skillet; mix.
Beat eggs well; add to milk, then add this to the flour and sugar.
Gradually beat until smooth and thick (if too thick, add little milk).
Make thinner than pie filling.
After cooked, add butter and vanilla.
Put vanilla wafers on bottom of bowl, sliced bananas on top of wafers, then pudding mixture.
Layer until all is gone.
End with pudding on top.
Beat egg whites stiff, and brown.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Add to water and boil until tender. Brown and drain hamburger.
Chop cabbage and add to pot with carrots.
Chop onion and add to pot.
Add tomatoes and green beans, including juice.
Add hamburger and seasonings to taste.
Simmer until raw vegetables are done.
Serve with hot biscuits or rolls. Serves 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: Drain whole kernel corn.
Place in bowl with creamed corn.
In processor or mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Mix in bowl with corn.
Pour mixture into 12 x 8-inch greased baking pan. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until when knife is inserted in center it comes out clean.

title: roast beef
directions: Brown all sides of roast in Dutch oven. Add beef consomme and water. Add bay leaf on top of roast. Cook in covered Dutch oven for several hours until meat shreds easily when cut across the grain of meat.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, oleo, 1 cup evaporated milk and vanilla. Allow this mixture to come to a rolling boil, stirring constantly. Add very slowly, while boiling, 1 cup evaporated milk.
Cook over moderate heat until mixture reaches a soft ball stage (232°).
Add pecans.
Pour into a large buttered pan.
Refrigerate overnight and cut into squares.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bananas and walnuts. Turn into 2 paper lined pans (either 9-inch round cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; frost with vanilla frosting.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Heat ingredients in crock-pot or microwave.
Dip apple slices in taffy.

title: cowbell meatballs
directions: Combine and shape into
1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in baking dish and brown them.
Makes 40 meatballs.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl combine the sugars and the oil.
Mix in the zucchini, vanilla, and the beaten eggs.
In a separate bowl mix together the flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, and the cinnamon.
Add to the zucchini mixture, mixing well.
Mix in the nuts last.
Pour into two large well-greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans and cool 15 minutes on rack.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: easy potato rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening. Add potatoes, salt and eggs.

title: peppermint ice cream
directions: Scald milk; add 1/4 cup crushed marshmallows and salt; stir until dissolved.
Freeze in refrigerator tray until firm, about 2 hours.
Beat in chilled bowl until smooth.
Fold in remaining candy and whipped cream; return to tray to freeze until firm, about 3 to 4 hours.

title: easy guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and mash with a fork, removing pit.
Add salsa, increasing to as much as 1/2 cup salsa, depending on
your taste. Best if served immediately.

title: salsa
directions: Chop zucchini, onion and jalapeno peppers.
Add salt.
Mix; let stand a few minutes, then drain.
Boil all ingredients 30 minutes.
Ladle into prepared jars.
Process in hot bath 10 minutes.
Yield: approximately 12 quarts.

title: chocolate-cherry cakes
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk, beating well.
Lastly, add cooled melted chocolate, nuts and cherries. Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting while still slightly warm.
Makes 20 cakes.

title: heritage dutch apple pie
directions: Combine apples, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon in bowl. Mix well. Arrange apple mixture in pie shell. Combine flour and 3/4 cup sugar in bowl. Add some cinnamon if desired. Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumbs over apples. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until top is golden brown and apples are tender.

title: mincemeat
directions: Pour boiling water through green tomatoes.
Mix and bring to a boil and let simmer 3 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan; set aside.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add sugar, eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Stir to blend.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: overnight pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni rinse and drain twice and let cool.
Place the lettuce in a 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with the cooked macaroni, then egg slices, ham strips, thawed peas and shredded cheese.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, green onion, mustard and hot pepper sauce.
Spread over top of seal, sealing to edge of dish.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with paprika and toss before serving.

title: marinated red cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and place in a bowl.
Add oil, vinegar, sugar, salts, pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Let stand several hours or overnight to allow flavors to mix.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and peanut butter.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix good, then add to dry ingredients.
Take small bits of dough and roll into small balls with hands.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: banana bread or muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350°.
Bake 1 hour for loaf and bake 17 minutes for muffins.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole dish at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: santa's special malted cocoa
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix the first two ingredients together with fork, then add remaining ingredients.
Fold with hands.
Roll out.
Bake at 350°. Yields 2 pies, top and bottom.

title: sausage and apple torta
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Unfold piecrust and use to line a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake according to package directions.
Set aside.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese in small bowl. Combine vanilla pudding and milk in small bowl.
Combine cream cheese mixture, pudding and Cool Whip in large bowl.
In large bowl, put layer of cookies, then layer of pudding mixture, etc. Be sure to end with cookies on top.

title: easy-bake apple pie
directions: Fill 9-inch pie plate (greased) 2/3 full of apples.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon.
In bowl combine melted margarine, 1 cup sugar, flour and egg.
Pour this mixture over apples evenly.
Spread to cover all the apples.
Preheat oven 10 minutes at 350°.
Bake 35 minutes until golden.

title: new orleans' bread pudding
directions: Note:
Optional 1 cup raisins added to custard mixture.

title: cream of persian vegetable soup
directions: Cook vegetables in water.
Saute celery and onion in butter and margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken bouillon cubes to flour mixture.
Add cold milk and stir until smooth.
Add ham, pepper and Accent.
Combine with vegetables and liquid in which vegetables were cooked.
Heat until steaming.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: dreamy italian salad dressing
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: barbecued pork
directions: Put meat in a roaster or deep pan. Mix onion, sugar, mustard, peppers, vinegar, water, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Pour over meat. Cover and cook in 350° oven 5 to 6 hours or until meat is ready to fall off the bones. Remove from oven and allow meat to cool in juices in refrigerator. When cool, skim off all fat; remove meat from bones and chop into small pieces, then put it back into sauce. Warm what you need and refrigerate the rest.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine
squash,
onions and carrots.
Sprinkle canning salt over
mixture;
let
stand overnight.
Drain and rinse in clear water.
Add
remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.	Pack
in hot jars and seal.
Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over
rhubarb;
drain.
Beat eggs well, then add sugar and flour.
Stir in rhubarb and pineapple last. The
water from the rhubarb and the pineapple juice can be used for tapioca pudding.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: In skillet, put margarine and melt over low heat.
Add onion; let cook a little.
Add broccoli, then add rice.
Put in cream of chicken soup.
Put in casserole dish.
Add grated cheese on top. Bake in a 325° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Start heating the oven to 375°.
Bring water, butter and salt to boil.
Add flour all at once, then beat over low heat until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a compact ball.
Remove from the heat; continue beating to cool mixture slightly, about 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
After last egg has been added, beat until mixture has a satinlike sheen.
Drop 5 or 6 mounds of batter 2 inches apart, swirling top of each mound.

title: scalloped potatoes n' onions
directions: Grease a baking dish with the bacon drippings.
Add in layers the potatoes, onion and bacon. Season with salt, pepper and soul food seasoning salt.
Pour on the milk. Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
The top should be golden brown.
You may add cheese the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: brownies
directions: Grease a 6 to 8-inch square pan; flour also.
Mix by hand all ingredients, then beat for 3 minutes.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) casserole with Pam vegetable spray.
Tear up pieces of bread into 1-inch pieces.
Place sausage in drainer basket (microwave-safe) and microwave on High 2 minutes. Stir and break into smaller pieces.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes longer or until no longer pink.
Sprinkle sausage over bread pieces.
Then sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Combine eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Beat until mixed well.
Pour mixture over bread, sausage and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until center is set.
If top begins to brown too much, cover with foil last 10 minutes of baking.
We enjoy this with banana bread, grits and grapefruit halves!

title: golden autumn salad
directions: Stir
gelatin
into boiling water until dissolved.
Add frozen orange
juice concentrate; stir until melted.
Stir in drained pineapple and oranges.
Pour into serving bowl or 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.	Cover; chill until set.

title: dilled potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, radishes and eggs in large bowl; toss lightly.
Soak onion in 1 tablespoon water, then add to potatoes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour over vegetables and toss until well mixed. Refrigerate several hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with paprika.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Drain blueberries and add enough water to blueberry juice to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil and stir in gelatin until dissolved. Add 1 1/2 cups cold water, pineapple and blueberries.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.
Prepare whipped topping mix as directions on package.
Blend with softened cheese and nuts.
Spread over congealed salad and chill for 2 hours.

title: mama's buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Melt butter.
Add all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake until brown at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crisco cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat well.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients into blender; blend on low until ice cubes are chopped up.

title: hot dill pickles
directions: Into clean quart jar, place 1 small clove garlic, 1 red pepper, 1 teaspoon alum, 1 teaspoon dill seed or some dill weed. Fill jar with cucumbers packed as tight as possible.
Fill all holes.
In pan, boil 13 cups water, 3 cups white vinegar and 1 cup plain salt. Pour over cucumbers and seal with hot lids.
If jars don't seal well, you can water bath them. Repeat process until all jars are filled with hot liquid.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed.
Gradually add sugars.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Add to butter mixture; mix and stir in oats.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: bean pot
directions: Fry hamburger and onion in skillet until done.
Set aside. Put pork and beans with drained butter and kidney beans in crock-pot. Add the hamburger, sugar, salt, cider and catsup. Stir well.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Turn on low and cook 3 to 4 hours.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix together 4x sugar, margarine, Cool Whip and egg yolks. Break (or crush) up Butterfingers.
Pinch pieces of cake.
Layer in dish.
Put some candy on top, then put some mixture on top of candy, then pinches of cake, then candy, then mixture until finished.
Top with some Cool Whip, if desired.

title: new zealand shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar well (this means the sugar has dissolved). Add sifted flour, cornstarch and salt. Knead well; roll out to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick. Cut into pieces; place on cold greased cookie sheet. Prick (fork holes) and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°. May also cook on one greased tin in which case, then cut into shapes while hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rum sauce
directions: Cook sugar with fruit juice or water for five minutes.
Add lemon juice and pour over top and sides of cake or custard.

title: meat loaf with sweet sauce
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can of tomato sauce in mixing bowl.
Toss together lightly with fork to combine.
Place in a shallow dish and shape into a loaf.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chocolate chips and 14 ounces bark on High for 2 minutes, then stir and microwave for 1 to 2 more minutes until smooth when stirred. Stir in marshmallows, Rice Krispies and peanuts. Pour into greased 12-inch pizza pan. Top with M&M's. Sprinkle with coconut. Microwave remaining bark and oil in 1-cup measure for 1 minute. Stir continuously until smooth. Drizzle over coconut. Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix and add sauce.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute meat, onion and pepper.
Mix with tomatoes, chili sauce, chili powder, garlic, cumin and 1 package cornmeal.
In separate bowl, combine 2 cups cornmeal, salt, eggs, cheeses and broth.
In baking dish, layer cornmeal crust and meat mixture ending with layer of cornmeal crust.
Bake.

title: golden chicken marengo
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in shortening.	Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.	Stir occasionally.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Layer vegetables in oblong 9 X 13 dish.
Lettuce must be dry (can be shaken in bag with paper towel to dry).
Spread mayonnaise and sugar mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon. Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature to soften.
Combine all but chili powder in electric mixer.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes to firm up for handling.

title: oven turkey salad
directions: Put first 6 ingredients into 12 quart casserole.
Prepare French gravy mix with milk instead of water.
Stir gravy into salad.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: lentil nut roast
directions: Boil lentils until well done.
Chop nuts fine.
Beat the egg and add to other ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in greased baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: favorite 2 egg cake
directions: Mix butter or Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Good with strawberries.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Shape dough according to variations and bake in a 400° oven on unbuttered baking sheets.
Chill dough.

title: liver pate
directions: Mix all of the above and chill till serving.

title: marilyn's strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together jello and 1 cup boiling water until dissolved. Add bananas, berries, pineapple and pecan pieces.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a 2-quart pan.
Let set in refrigerator for 30 minutes. Top with sour cream.
Add remaining mixture.
Cool in refrigerator about 3 hours before serving.

title: canned beef
directions: Pack beef tightly in pint canning jars.
Add 3/4 teaspoon uniodized table salt to each pint.
Seal jars.
Place in pressure canner with 10 pounds weight and process for 75 minutes.
Good for beef and noodles, barbecue beef or hot beef and gravy.

title: chicken or turkey divan(microwave)
directions: Place broccoli in casserole dish; cover.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.
If using fresh broccoli, cook in 1/4 cup water for 5 to 6 minutes on High.
Drain.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
In a small mixing bowl, blend other ingredients except crackers.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over the top.
Cover.
Microwave 6 to 7 minutes.
The flavors seem to blend better if you mix this the day before.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all of the ingredients well with a spoon.
Pour into a Pam-sprayed casserole, 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: frozen mocha cheesecake
directions: Mix cookie crumbs,
sugar
and margarine in small bowl. Pat mixture firmly in bottom and sides of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk and syrup.
Dissolve
coffee
in
water
and add to Eagle Brand mixture.
Mix
well.
Fold
in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Garnish
with
additional
crumbs
if
desired. Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: mashed potato and cream cheese casserole
directions: Drain a can of sweet potatoes.
Roll potatoes in mixture of flour and white sugar.
Make syrup of brown sugar, butter and a little water. Bring to a boil and pour over potatoes.
Place in a 325° oven just long enough until all is hot.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken until done; cool, then bone chicken.
Unroll the crescent rolls.
On each triangle place some chicken and 1 slice of cheese.
Roll up long side first and place in baking dish.
Heat cream of chicken soup, 1 cup milk and remaining cheese over low heat.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour over roll-ups, but don't cover with mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Brown onion in oil in a Dutch oven.
Add seasonings and stir. Add chicken and brown 10 minutes.
Add water.
Cover and simmer slowly until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Put 3 Tbsp. flour in a bowl, add enough water to make a smooth paste, then add the sour cream and stir well.
Add the sour cream mixture to drippings in pot.
Return chicken.

title: chive potato latkes(potato pancakes)
directions: Place half each of the potatoes, water and onion in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed until finely grated, about 20 seconds; drain.
Pour potato mixture into large bowl. Repeat with remaining potatoes, water and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: watauga medical center low-fat chocolate cake
directions: Mix water, puree, egg whites and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add sugar.
Mix dry and wet ingredients until well blended and smooth.

title: pork roast easy deluxe
directions: Heat oil in heavy Dutch oven until hot.
Add roast and brown quickly on all sides.
Remove pan from heat; remove roast from pan and drain oil off.
Rub roast all over with dried sage (3 to 4 tablespoons) and salt and pepper.
Return roast to Dutch oven and pour 1 can of consomme in pan.
Roast in oven (350°) for 1 hour and 30 minutes (covered).
During last half hour, add 1 can of dry (or sweet) vermouth and mushrooms, sliced thickly.
Roast until done; enjoy!

title: paradise salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Let set overnight.
Add whipped cream and mix.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Heat
milk
to warm, not hot.
Mix sugar and cornstarch and add
slowly to milk, stirring and cook until hot.
Slowly stir
in the
well-beaten
egg
yolk.
Cook
until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in coconut and flavoring. Pour
into
crust
and top with meringue made from the egg whites. Sprinkle with coconut and brown in the oven.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Layer chicken in greased baking dish.
Layer broccoli and onion.
Mix soup and mayonnaise. Pour over chicken, broccoli and onion.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; discard skin and bones.
Save juice.
Flake salmon and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack firmly into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until light brown and firm.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add egg and mix well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into well-greased 11 1/2 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Top with blueberries.
Sprinkle Cinnamon Crumbs over berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut in squares. Serve warm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cajun seasoning mix
directions: Keep in a small jar, covered, for future use.

title: light-as-a-feather doughnuts
directions: Scald milk and stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, egg and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured board. Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in bowl, cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and roll out about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with donut cutter.
Place on floured sheet pans.
Let rise until double.
Fry in oil at 375°.
Dip in glaze made of 2 cups of powdered sugar, 1/3 cup milk and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together.
Add eggs one at a time; beat after each egg.
Add salt, flour and flavoring.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 320° in greased tube pan.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and
keep
in
refrigerator.
Drain all juice out of oranges and pineapple.
Mix jello in dry.

title: creamy deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; mash in small bowl. Stir in dressing, relish and seasonings until smooth.
Spoon into centers of egg whites.
Cover.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Heat and serve.

title: hootenanny pancakes
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Beat ingredients and pour in pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Heat the oil in a frying pan.
Fry the chicken and onion, sprinkle with garlic salt.
Keep turning until chicken is light brown.
Add chopped celery, mushrooms, soy sauce and chicken broth. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch and stir until thickened.
Add cashew nuts and stir.
Add dried chilies.
Spoon over rice.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then store in jars or closed containers.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of water or to taste.

title: pudding surprise
directions: Mix to directions on package.
Spread on top of the cheese mix.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: grilled red snapper
directions: Cut fish into serving-size portions.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Arrange fish on grill.
Brush generously with sauce.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes and turn.
Brush fish with sauce and cook for about 7 minutes or until fish flakes.
Do not overcook.

title: spuds hot potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes in large pieces.
Boil until soft and done.
When soft, drain and mash.
Add all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: spicy chocolate bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients, add chocolate pieces or reserve chocolate and sprinkle over dough before baking. Spread into 2 ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pans or 3 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pans.
Bake in oven at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cut into 80 bars and cool.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients, coat wings.
Bake 350° for 2-3 hours. Turn 2-3 times.

title: zucchini surprise
directions: Clean and wash vegetables. Chop.
Cook zucchini until half done.
Add onion, tomatoes and season to taste.
Cook until done. Serve.

title: fresh stuffed crabs
directions: Boil crab in black pepper and water for 30 minutes.
Cool. Pry crabs open with a knife.
Remove all white meat and a little crab fat.
Set aside.
Scrub shells in clean water.
Drop in boiling water with a pinch of soda, about 20 minutes.
Cool shells before adding stuffing.
Saute onion, green pepper, garlic and celery in oil for about 5 minutes.
Add crabmeat and brown.
Add a little butter, crab fat and water to moisten, then add red pepper, salt and Kitchen Bouquet (this will turn slightly brown). Cover and simmer 30 minutes (or until water is absorbed).
Mix with dry dressing and stuff shells.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Can be frozen but omit bread crumbs on top.
You can refrigerate overnight and then bake.

title: layered green salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed (twice) in oblong dish.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Scrub lemons; roll on counter to soften slightly.
Trim ends. Cut fruit into very thin slices; discard seeds.
Place slices in a wide bottomed pitcher.
Cover with sugar.
Let stand until sugar starts to dissolve; press with a wooden spoon to hasten process. Add ice cubes and water; stir.
Strain into glass.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown together in bacon grease the mushrooms, rice, onion and pepper.
Add tomatoes, boiling water, salt and pepper.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In a large nonstick pan, heat oil and add cabbage, carrots, bell pepper and onions.
Toss vegetables frequently with spatula. Add sugar, crumbled bacon, pepper sauce, salt, pepper and 6 to 8 teaspoons bacon grease.
Cook about 15 minutes.
If you want crispy vegetables, do not cover pan.
Cook over medium heat until desired crispness.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, together to form dough. Roll into 2 long rolls.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, cut into 1/8-inch circles.
Beat egg whites lightly and brush onto each cheese circle.
Place a pecan half on each circle before the egg whites begin to dry.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Boil in 3 cups water.
Add salt and pepper.
Place bread crumbs in casserole.
Add eggplant, onion and pepper; mix thoroughly.
Add 2 eggs, beaten in milk.
Pour over mixture.
Put more crumbs on top and put 2 tablespoons melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix all in a pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Put in jars and can.

title: red snapper mozart
directions: Marinate snapper in a combination of salt, pepper, lemon juices and Worcestershire sauce in a baking dish.
Remove fish and dip in flour to coat.
Melt butter in skillet.
Brown snapper slowly on both sides.
Transfer fish to a two-quart baking dish and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
(Total cooking time for skillet and oven is 15 minutes.)

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cottage salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello well.
Fold in Cool Whip and oranges.
Chill and serve.

title: stuffed cabbage (helupkies)
directions: Wash head of cabbage.
Cut the stem from the head of cabbage deep enough to start a separation of the very outer leaves from the core.
Carefully pull away the outer leaves.
Continue to remove the leaves until you have enough for the recipe.
If the leaves are not coming off, you may dip the head of cabbage in boiling water to loosen 3 or 4 leaves at a time.
Once you have the leaves you are going to use, steam them until tender.
(In order to steam, fill a Dutch oven 1 to 2-inches with water.
Place a colander inside and then the leaves in the colander.
Put the lid on and boil the water for 5 to 10 minutes.)

title: parmesan cheese
directions: In a bowl, mix mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and oregano together.
Place chicken in baking dish or pan.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: ms. pam's favorite cheese ball
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with 1 package chopped dried beef, chopped onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Form ball and cover with second package of beef.
Chill and serve with any kind of crackers.
Great for parties!

title: turtle stew
directions: Cook turtle in water until it is well done and pick the meat off the bones.
Cook potatoes and onions together.
Mix all ingredients in large pot.
This includes cooked ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour; keep stirring so milk won't burn, but don't boil.

title: refried beans
directions: Wash and soak beans in water overnight.
When ready to cook, put beans, onion, spices and water in large pot; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until a thick batter consistency (about 4 to 5 hours).
Store in desired size of bowls and freeze.

title: corny cornmeal pudding
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in bacon fat.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
In a baking dish, approximately 17 x 11 x 2 1/2-inch, bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into ungreased loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss spaghetti with ingredients listed.
Add assorted chopped raw vegetables (optional).
Chill and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Dice bell pepper and onion. Cut bacon about 1/2-inch.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: mozzarella macaroni
directions: Cut cabbage head in half and remove core.
Cut cabbage halves into pieces and parboil until about half done.
Add macaroni and cook to desired tenderness.
Drain and add butter, cheeses (I use half of each kind) and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and serve.

title: ranch house stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Wash, slit side and remove seeds from jalapeno peppers while holding pepper under running water, leaving stem intact.
Let dry completely.
Stuff each pepper with a teaspoon or more of pimento cheese and close so no cheese can be seen.

title: shawn's hamburger gravy patties
directions: Shape hamburger into patties.
Fry hamburger patties until half-way done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain all grease off patties.
Add 1 can of soup and add 1/2 can of water or milk. Cover and let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple juice into saucepan.
Heat juice and dissolve jello in 3/4 of the hot juice. Dissolve cheese in remaining juice. Mix together all ingredients except cola drinks. Cool.
Add cola drinks slowly. Congeal.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Heat sugar and margarine in saucepan until melted.
Add rest of ingredients, except ice cream.
Stir well.
Press 1/2 of mixture in an 11 x 7-inch pan (or 9 x 9-inch pan).
Spread with ice cream.
Top with rest of mixture.
Freeze.
Before serving, remove dessert from freezer approximately 20 minutes to soften slightly.

title: twisted lemonade twist
directions: Fill a glass with crushed ice and add vodka and Triple Sec. Top off with sweet and sour mix. Add a lemon wedge for garnish and serve. Serves 1.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar. Add cream cheese, salt, vanilla, lemon juice and almond extract. Blend in sour cream. Pour into graham crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until just set. Chill at least 4 hours. Top with strawberries, cherries or blueberries when serving. Makes 12 servings.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain excess grease. Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, sprayed with Pam, place half the tortillas which have been torn into strips.
Pour half of the meat mixture over this and top with half of the grated cheese.
Use the last half of the torn tortillas on top of first meat and cheese mixture.
Top with remaining meat and cheese mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: easy pleasing meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix 1 cup water and all ingredients except 1/4 cup of barbecue sauce.
Shape meat mixture into an oval loaf in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining barbecue sauce.
Bake 1 hour or until center is no longer pink.
Makes 8 servings.

title: no-sugar cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries and water in a large pot and place on stove on "high" until the berries pop.
If they don't all pop, use a potato masher to crush the ones that did not pop.
(Use pot lid while cooking.)
Then cook over a low heat for about 20 minutes without lid.
Start the timing when the berries start to cook, not when you put the pot on the burner.

When cooked for 20 minutes, add 14 packets of Equal sweetener (each packet to equal 2 teaspoons sugar) and 2 packages of unflavored, unsweetened gelatin that has been softened in cold water and then melted over hot water.
Stir this in and put mixture in containers.
Keep in refrigerator.
Use as regular cranberry relish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Microwave broccoli using package directions.
Combine mushrooms and butter in glass dish.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Add rice and broccoli.
Blend soup and Cheez Whiz in small bowl.
Add to broccoli mixture; mix well.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.

title: never fail chocolate cream pie
directions: Sift together in pan the flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add milk, evaporated milk and egg yolks.
Cook until desired thickness in a large saucepan. Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine. Pour into a 9-inch baked shell. Top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream well the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour, sifted with soda, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Beat egg whites; fold into mixture.
Makes 4 layers.
Bake in greased and floured pans for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: danish potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and gradually beat in well beaten eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Take off heat and beat in salad dressing.
Toss together remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing over and toss gently.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: Cook ground chuck in a large ovenproof skillet with lid over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well and pat meat dry with paper towels.
Wipe skillet with a paper towel.
Return ground chuck to skillet and layer potatoes, carrots, onion, green pepper and tomatoes over top.
Sprinkle with pepper and basil.
Cover with ovenproof lid and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yields 8 servings (3/4 cup each). Calories: 147.
Exchanges:
1 starch; 1 medium-fat meat.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and water.
Dissolve cornstarch in 3/4 cup water; add to syrup mixture.
Cook about 10 minutes until clear.
Stir to keep from lumping.
Blend in salt, lemon juice and coloring; cool.
Pour over berries.
Put in baked pie crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: beef and beans in the skillet
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in beans and barbecue sauce or ketchup. Let it get hot through. Sprinkle on cheese and let stay on low heat until cheese is melted.

title: mushroom and cheese roll
directions: Chop onions and mushrooms and saute in butter. Add Allouette cheese to the mixture. Open 1 puff pastry and spread mixture on the pastry sheet. Roll up jellyroll style. Slice roll (approximately 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick slices). Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes. (Follow directions on puff pastry box.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Spread uncooked rice in flat baking dish.
Pour melted oleo over rice.
Next, spread squash and onion slices.
Mix soup and water well; pour over all.
Bake at 325° until tender.
Sprinkle 1 cup toasted croutons on top after done.

title: fudgy scotch squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, mix all of the ingredients.
Press mixture into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown, depends on oven. Cool completely (about 45 minutes).
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Very rich!

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add oleo, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add flour, make dough firm.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Let rise to double in size.
Knead again and make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350°.

title: alaska sheet cake
directions: Bring oleo and water to a boil.
Add next 4 ingredients to water and oleo mixture.
Beat eggs, buttermilk and soda; add to other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: brown rice salad with grilled chicken
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients.
In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine the vinegar, oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper; shake well. Pour over rice mixture and toss to coat.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: sherry-sage turkey
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
In bowl, combine first 6 ingredients and 2 tablespoons sherry.
Rub butter mixture over and under turkey skin.
Roast 1 hour; reduce oven to 325 degrees.
Cook 1 hour more, or until internal temperature reaches 180 degrees.
Baste with pan juices every 30 minutes.
Separate fat from pan juices.
In saucepan, heat 6 tablespoons fat over medium-high heat.
Whisk in flour; cook 5 minutes, or until brown.
Slowly add reserved pan juices remaining sherry and broth, stirring constantly.
Cook gravy 5 minutes, or until thickened.
Makes 12 servings and 3 cups gravy.

title: creamy oven potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and cook potatoes on medium heat for 10 minutes.
In small saucepan, melt butter and saute onions. Add flour, milk and salt.
Continue cooking on medium heat.
Stir so mixture does not stick.
When it is thickened, pour over potatoes in greased casserole dish.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Spread frozen potatoes in ungreased glass 9 x 12-inch dish. Mix next 3 ingredients together.
Spread over potatoes.
Cover with crushed chips.
Sprinkle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Add milk and flour, alternating.
Add vanilla and black walnuts. Bake in tube pan at 300 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: veggie lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Blanch veggies; drain.
Mix Ricotta, 1/2 cup Romano and Mozzarella with eggs, 1/2 of the basil and 1/2 of the parsley.
Quickly sear in 4 tablespoons olive oil, the veggies, garlic, remaining basil and parsley.
Set aside.

title: republican soup
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in frying pan and cook until hamburger changes color.
Add hamburger mixture to next 6 ingredients, then potatoes.
Cook for 1 hour, then add corn.
Let simmer or slow boil for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Makes enough for several people or to freeze.
Can add pintos or kidney.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash; add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all
together.
Store
in plastic gallon container. To serve, add 2 tablespoons to cup of hot water.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn flakes and margarine together and place in a buttered baking dish; crumble 2 cups corn flakes over potato mixture.
Drizzle with 1/4 pound melted margarine over top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package; drain and chop.
Set aside.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and add onion in saucepan.
Let brown.
Add milk and flour.
Let come to a boil. Set aside.

title: corn pudding
directions: Soak crackers in the milk.
Mix rest of the ingredients.
Add to soaked crackers.
Bake in greased casserole 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco chicken
directions: Chop chicken and mix with other ingredients except 1 cup cheese.
Line a 7 x 11-inch dish with tortilla chips, overlapping and standing up the sides.
Pour chicken mixture over chips and cover with remaining cup of cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, butter, peanut butter and vanilla and shape into balls.
Melt paraffin and melt chips in that.
Dip each ball in mixture.
Put on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: baked french fries
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 3/8-inch strips.
Put in cold water. When ready to cook, dry strips on a towel.
Spread in pan sprayed with Pam and toss with seasoning of choice.
Bake 30 minutes at 450° to 475°.
Turn after 15 minutes to brown evenly.
If crispier fries are desired, place under broiler for 1 to 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings (approximately 15 fries); 50 cal, less than 1 g fat.

title: irish tea cake
directions: Mix all together (melt margarine).
Put in round tin (grease and flour it first).
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.
Make the sign of the cross (with a knife) before baking.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and onion; slice. Mix vinegar, sugar and water in medium mixing bowl. Add cucumber and onion. Make sure they are covered with mixture.

title: quick and easy pound cake
directions: Cream
Crisco
and
sugar well.
Add eggs, beating well after each
one.	Add flour and mix well.
Put into Bundt pan; bake in 325°
oven	for
1 hour and 10 minutes.
Put into cold oven.
Do not open oven until cake is done.

title: kol dolmer
directions: Mix thoroughly steak, pork, onion, salt, sugar and pepper. Boil rice.
Wilt cabbage leaves by putting in boiling water.
Put some meat and rice mixture in wilted cabbage leaves and roll into balls securely.
Repeat until all of mixture is used.

title: california coleslaw(no fat, sugar-free)
directions: Combine cabbages, carrot, green and red peppers, onion and parsley in a large bowl, stirring well.
Set aside.
Combine vinegar, Italian dressing, sugar substitute, salt and pepper in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Combine chicken, sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Put in casserole dish; top with Cheddar cheese and crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake until bubbly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill 5 to 10 minutes.

title: banana wafer pudding
directions: Mix all together vanilla pudding, milk and condensed milk. Chill 5 minutes.
Mix in whipping cream.
In a large bowl, pour:

title: scripture cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and spices together 3 times.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add honey, almonds, raisins and figs and mix well.
Add flour, alternately with water, a small amount at a time, beating well after each addition.
Turn into 2 greased 9 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch pans (loaf) which have been greased, lined with paper and greased again.
Bake in 350° oven about 2 1/2 hours.

title: custard's kids soup
directions: Mix the books and the students in a large classroom.
Add the paper and the pencils.
Mix well.
Mix together the chalkboard, numbers and problems.
Add this to the student mixture.
Stir in the principal and the students.
Boil for 180 days at full steam. Serve with 2 cups of love and laughter.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix all the other ingredients in a bowl and pour into the pan.
Do not stir, but pat down.
Bake 350° until done (about 25 minutes)

title: baskin robbins dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread this into pan.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine al ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel.
Cut potatoes in halves and place in a baking dish.
Spread or dot butter over top.
Add salt.
Pour corn syrup over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pralines
directions: In skillet, put 1/2 cup sugar; melt and brown.
In saucepan, bring 3 cups sugar and water to boil.
Pour in slowly the browned sugar, stirring all the time.
Add pecans, vanilla and 1 teaspoon butter.
Cook to soft ball stage (not over).
Cool and beat until creamy.
Drop by tablespoon on foil paper.

title: diet soup
directions: Cut vegetables and cover with water in a large pot.
Boil for 10 minutes. Cover.
Lower heat and simmer until vegetables are soft. Season with soup mix while boiling.

title: microwave brownie s'mores
directions: Place 2 brownies on microwave-safe plate.
Arrange 3 candies on each brownie.
Microwave on High 20 to 30 seconds or just until candies soften.
Gently spread melted candy on top of each brownie.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Pour soups and rice over pork chops.
Add water to cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peas and peanuts salad
directions: Mix together peas, peanuts and mayonnaise.
Add a little minced onion and celery.
Mix and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight.
Use no juice.

title: grilled garlic shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp in cold water and dry well.
Pour butter and olive oil into a 3-quart shallow bowl.
Add shallots.
Chop garlic with salt on a cutting board (this helps eliminate the strong garlic aftertaste).
Add garlic and salt mixture to bowl.
Roll shrimp in this mixture until well coated.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and parsley.
Marinate at least 30 minutes, turning shrimp several times.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add spices.
Beat thoroughly and add rest of ingredients.
Stir to blend well.
Be sure to flour nuts.
Place into greased loaf pan (Bundt).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken basque
directions: Rub chicken with lemon and salt; brown in olive oil.
Cook with lid on until tender.
In another skillet, saute onions, green pepper, garlic and eggplant.
Remove to a large casserole; cook mushrooms and tomatoes.
Add to casserole.
Bone chicken and add to casserole.
In chicken skillet, add flour, bouillon and 1/2 cup white wine.
Add to casserole.
Put in a 325° oven for 2 hours. Add 1/2 cup wine during last 1/2 hour of cooking.
Serve with rice.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour in greased jellyroll pan. Sprinkle nuts and brown sugar over top of batter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue wings
directions: Combine chili sauce, honey, soy, mustard, vinegar, hot - pepper sauce, onion, and salt in a large bowl.
Add the wings; toss to coat.
Place on baking sheet.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Dip toasted bread in butter.
Alternate layers of bread with the raisins, cheese, nuts and bananas in baking dish.
It is not necessary to remove the crust from the bread except for appearance's sake, so I suggest you remove them only when you want to be fancy!

title: pecans dreams
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and 1 cup flour until coarse meal texture. Spread in ungreased 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Combine 2 tablespoons remaining ingredients.
Spread over oleo mixture. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour over meat loaf in oven; continue baking 1 1/2 hours longer, basting occasionally.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, pineapple and one cup pecans. Shape into ball. Roll in remaining pecans. Chill and serve.

title: maryann's snappers
directions: In a double boiler spray top with Pam or other vegetable spray oil.
Bring water to a boil.
Lower flame and put caramel and crushed pecans in top pan.
Heat until caramel melts so that it may be stirred to mix the nuts thoroughly.
As soon as the nuts are well mixed into the caramel, remove from heat and allow to cool until it is workable by hand.
When cool enough to handle, spray hands with Pam and spoon onto a cookie sheet.
I use 12 x 12-inch pieces of cardboard covered with freezer paper, slick side up. Spoon the size you want.
If you want bite sized pieces, use a teaspoon, otherwise a small tablespoon.
When you fill the cookie sheet/cardboard place them into the refrigerator immediately until they are cool and hard.

title: ranch baked beans
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck.
Add all other ingredients and bake, covered, 30 minutes at 400°.

title: true fudge, fudge brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips, into a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, stirring until melted. Cool for 5 minutes, stir and spread over cooled brownies.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli, onion, bacon and Mozzarella cheese in a large bowl.
Make dressing with remaining ingredients and pour over mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight. Serves a crowd.
Great for a ladies luncheon.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, butter and flour.
Blend well.
Add pineapple, cherries, coconut and cherry juice.
Mix well.
Add lemon extract, mix well again.
Place in floured and greased pan. Put in preheated oven at 275 degrees for 2 1/2 hours.
Turn upside down to cool.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix margarine, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Add oatmeal, coconut, nuts and dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Do not over bake!
Makes 4 dozen.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate before use.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as directed on package. Drain well and return to pot. Add remaining ingredients and salt and pepper to taste. Spread into casserole dish.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add egg and beat.
Add flour sifted with baking powder, salt and milk a little at a time.
Pour thin batter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread 2 to 3 boxes of berries on top.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until golden brown.

title: green bean soup(grun bohne suppe; a family favorite)
directions: Assemble all ingredients.
Saute onion and bacon until translucent.
Add potatoes and water; cook over medium heat until potatoes are done.
Add string beans; continue to cook until tender.
Just before serving, add small amount (dollop) of cream or milk to each bowl.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with melted butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake potatoes for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly brown.
Check with fork.

title: biscotti(italian toast)
directions: Grease hands!
Mix and form small loaves about 4 x 12-inch. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly.
Cut into slices. Put back on cookie sheet and toast for about 10 minutes.
Turn to toast other side.

title: pineapple-carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside. Combine cooking oil, eggs and sugar in bowl; beat with mixer at medium speed 2 minutes.
Blend in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, carrots, pineapple, coconut and walnuts to mixture, blending well. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Place pan on rack, immediately pour vanilla glaze over cake.
Cool completely, makes 16 servings.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Soak the gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks slightly in a saucepan; add sugar and mix.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Stir and cook mixture until thickened. Remove from heat; add soaked gelatin and stir until dissolved. Fold in whipped cream and remaining ingredients.
Chill about 24 hours.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: To Make White Sauce: Melt butter over low heat in a heavy saucepan. Use a wooden spoon or whisk to stir. Blend in flour and seasonings. Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Makes 1 cup. (Double White Sauce recipe.)

title: savory foldovers
directions: Sift flour into a bowl and rub in the butter or margarine until mixture resembles bread crumbs. Work in cream cheese and chill overnight.
Mix ham with the dill and Worcestershire sauce. Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease several baking sheets. Divide dough into even number of pieces; the foldovers can be small or large.
Roll out each piece on a well floured surface and cut out a circle with a cookie cutter.
Spread each circle with filling and fold over to make half circle. Sprinkle with poppy seed or paprika.
The foldovers may be shaped in advance and kept chilled until ready to bake. Serve hot or cold.
Makes about 28.

title: peanut butter bark cookies
directions: Spread the flat side of a vanilla wafer with chunky or creamy peanut butter.
Top with a second wafer.
Dip into melted candy coating.
Cool on wax paper until hard.

title: shrimp scampi pasta
directions: Saute shrimp in margarine and garlic.
Toss over high heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over cooked pasta.
Top with fresh diced tomatoes and parsley.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, drained pineapple, mayonnaise and dehydrated onions.
Add confectioners sugar, if you like a sweeter cheese ball.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped pecans until ball is covered.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and soda and add eggs and juice of fruit cocktail.
Mix well and fold in fruit cocktail.
Pour into greased and floured pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top before baking.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: hamburger cutlets parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, lightly toss beef with parsley, seasoned salt and pepper until well combined.
Shape into 6 patties, 1/2 inch thick.
Roll each patty in flour, coating both sides; then dip in egg; finally roll in crumbs.

In hot oil in large skillet, cook patties until nicely browned on both sides. Arrange in one layer in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top each patty with a slice of Mozzarella; pour spaghetti sauce over all; then sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 25 minutes, or until sauce is bubbly and cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: country apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In
a
large
bowl, combine cake mix, margarine and egg.	Beat
at
low
speed
until
crumbly. Press in an ungreased 9 x
13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling on top. Combine brown sugar,
nuts	and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples. In a small bowl,
blend
sour cream, egg and vanilla. Pour over brown sugar mixture.
Bake	at
for
to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: joan's homemade soup
directions: Cut meat in small pieces and cook in water with salt, pepper, onion and green onions.
(I like to cook mine in a pressure cooker.)
When nearly cooked, add carrots, potatoes, sweet potatoes, plantains and celery soup.
Continue cooking, adding water if needed to cover vegetables.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, oil and apples.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Use 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: billy goats
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and sour milk.
Combine soda, baking powder, cinnamon, flour, nuts and dates; add to the creamed mixture.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
They are very good cookies.

title: karo krazy krunch
directions: Place popped popcorn in large bowl or on cookie sheet. Combine sugar, margarine and syrup in 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling, stirring occasionally to soft crack on candy thermometer. Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Coat well and stir.
Spread out to dry on wax paper.
Break apart and store tightly covered.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all together with spoon.
Put in refrigerator to chill before serving.

title: fresh flour tortillas
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add shortening and warm water.
Knead dough until well mixed.
Form into 3-inch ball.
Roll out into round flat cakes, about 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick and cook on very hot griddle, first one side and then the other until both sides are spotted medium brown.

title: roquefort steak
directions: Wipe meat with paper towels. Mix cheese, garlic, pepper, salt, soy sauce, coffee, Worcestershire sauce and oil in a blender. Pour over steak, rubbing marinade in with hands. Marinate several hours or overnight.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix in chips and stir until melted. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a bowl, beat together the cream cheese, margarine or butter and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in enough remaining powdered sugar to make frosting of spreading consistency.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine; add sugars and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in oatmeal.
Roll into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press dough with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Yield:
5 dozen cookies.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use it to baste your favorite meats.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce and cool. Beat with beater until completely blended.
Mix in crushed pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix chicken flavor pack from Ramen Noodles with oil, vinegar and sugar.
Blend with whisk.
Toss in remaining ingredients except Ramen Noodles.
Mix well.
Crumble Ramen Noodles and mix together. Cool 30 minutes in refrigerator before serving.

title: apple pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook apples with butter in a saucepan until barely tender.
Do not overcook.
Combine undrained apples with bread, sugar, milk, lemon rind, dates, salt and vanilla. Beat egg yolks with a fork and stir into bread mixture.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into bread mixture. Pour into greased 2-quart glass casserole; sprinkle with nutmeg. Place casserole in a large pan containing 1-inch deep hot water. Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter, saute garlic and onion until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute. Gradually add milk, stirring until mixture boils and thickens. Spoon 1/4 of sauce into deep casserole.
Add half the potatoes and carrots.
Top with turkey and half the cheese.
Add remaining potatoes and carrots.
Top with remaining cheese.
Pour remaining sauce over all.
Bake, uncovered, 1 to
1 1/2 hours, until all vegetables are tender..
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes, then serve.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.
Add 1 cup frozen strawberries and
stir
well.
Bake
in
2 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry chocolate bar
directions: In mixing bowl combine cake mix, pie filling, extract and eggs.
Blend well by hand (no mixer).
Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, cool slightly.

title: grandma's turn cakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Gradually add water to make a dough. Fry in oil until golden brown. Great for breakfast with butter and honey on top.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion and cook gently about 5 minutes.
Blend in flour; stir in tomato sauce and heat to boiling.
Mix in lemon juice, salt, pepper, sugar, horseradish, mustard and chicken.
Cover and cook gently, about 15 minutes. Serve on warmed hamburg buns.

title: hello dolly
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Lay remaining ingredients in pan in order given.
Cover with Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: ham roll
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix cheese and horseradish sauce together.
Mix milk to make a good spread.
Add olives.
Spread mixture over ham slices and roll to form a roll. Use toothpicks to hold together.
Chill.
Before serving, cut into bite size pieces.

title: chili clam dip
directions: With electric mixer or rotary beater, gradually blend soup, chili sauce and onion into cream cheese until just smooth (overbeating makes dip thin).
Chill.
Serve with crackers or chips.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts and raisins and mix until well blended. Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Combine green pepper, pimento, celery, onion and cheese.
Mix well.
Add peas, eggs and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Stir in red pepper and salt.
Serve on bed of crisp lettuce.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Put dill, garlic, pepper and alum in a jar.
Pack in cucumbers.
Heat liquid and pour over cucumbers and seal.
If you have any liquid left, save for the next time.

title: chemical garden
directions: Put coal and a little water in a bowl.
Mix salt, water, bluing and ammonia.
Add food color by drops.
Add slowly to the coal and water!

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli and onion in margarine until tender.
Add grated cheese until well mixed.
Add soup and milk and pour into greased pan and add Minute rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Mix together grated carrots and raisins.
Add just enough mayonnaise to hold mixture together.
Serve over lettuce leaves.

title: soy-glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain and reserve 1/4 cup juice from pineapple; set pineapple slices aside.
In open roasting pan mix pineapple juice, soy sauce, instant minced onions, ginger and garlic powder. Add chicken, turning to coat pieces well.
Arrange chicken, skin side up; bake 50 to 60 minutes, until chicken is fork-tender, spooning pan juices over chicken occasionally during baking.
When chicken is done, add pineapple slices to roasting pan; heat through, about 5 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown together the sausage, onion and green pepper.
Add the mushroom soup, 1 can water and the instant rice.
Cook until thickened.
Season with the garlic salt, celery salt and salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: easter paska
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Measure 1 1/2 cups warm water, 1 cup milk, lard, salt and sugar into a bowl.
Add the yeast mixture.
Beat 4 egg yolks and 2 whole eggs and add to milk mixture.
Add flour 2 cups at a time.
Keep adding and working in until dough is no longer sticky.
Grease large bowl or pan.
Let dough rise in pan in warm place for 2 hours.
Punch down lightly. Let rise 45 minutes longer.
Form into loaves.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Brush with egg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pieces of dough may be rolled into long strips and then braided.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: sombrero spread
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain thoroughly.
Stir in catsup, chili powder and salt.
Mash beans and add to meat mixture.
Heat before serving and garnish with cheese and olives.
Makes 3 cups dip.
Serve in fondue pot.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Combine white sugar, brown sugar and cocoa.
Mix well and sprinkle over batter.
Pour 1 cup water (cold) over batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: kool-aid cookies
directions: Chill.
Roll into balls, then roll balls into sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg and water.
Add vanilla and stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until almost no indentation remains when touched (10 to 12 minutes).
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.

title: refrigerator pickles #1
directions: Sprinkle salt over veggies and let stand 1 hour.
Drain well. Mix other ingredients and pour over veggies.
Refrigerate overnight.	These will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Make biscuits using flour, crisco and milk to desired consistency.
Bake at 350° until bottom of biscuits are brown but not completely done.
Boil chicken breasts until done.
Save 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Mix veggies, soup, and 1 pkg of cheese, cooked chicken and chicken broth.
Mix well.
Cut biscuits in half, put in baking dish with the middle part down, golden brown side up; save top half of biscuit for the topping of the pot pie.
Pour vegetable mixture over biscuits.
Pour 1 pkg of cheese over the mixture, add biscuit top and bake 20 minutes.

title: glorious morning muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir only until wet and dry ingredients are combined.
Spoon into greased or paper lined muffin tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle tops with sugar before baking, if desired.
Serves 24.

title: cream cheese twists
directions: Mix all but jelly and sugar.
Form ball.
Pinch off small balls. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out in powdered sugar covered board.
Fill with jelly; fold and seal.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: heavenly cheese salad
directions: Heat water; add lemon jello. Beat in the cream cheese. Beat well and chill. Add drained pineapple and pecans. When partially thickened, fold in dream or cool whip. Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Beat puddings into milk.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Spread desired amount of Cool Whip on top.
Decorate with nuts.

title: janice's chicken(crock-pot)
directions: Place place chicken breasts (boneless) in crock-pot which has been brushed with melted butter and sprinkle with dry Italian dressing.
Cook 5 to 6 hours on low.
Drain broth from chicken and use 1/4 cup to make sauce.
Use the rest to make rice.

title: creamy cabbage
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat milk until bubbles appear around the edge.
Add cabbage and simmer 10 minutes.
Blend together margarine and flour.
Add to milk and cabbage, stirring constantly.
Add more milk if too thick.

title: "cedric"
directions: Fry ground beef and onion until meat is brown; drain.
In baking dish, layer chopped cabbage, cheese and ground beef; cover with tomato sauce which has been mixed with the 1/2 can water. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Cook onions until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low flame for 10 minutes.

title: instant pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk on low speed until blended.
Add pumpkin, spice and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set.
Garnish with rest of Cool Whip.

title: marzipan(strawberries)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape as strawberries.
Add stems of whole cloves or angelica or use confectioners sugar and water colored green with food color.
Make thick from leaves, use green toothpicks for stems.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add cheese spread; stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Serve with vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: mom's soft raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in small saucepan; bring to a boil. Cook for three minutes; remove from the heat and let cool (do not drain).
In a mixing bowl, cream Crisco; gradually add sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture and blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yield:
About 6 dozen cookies.

title: burritos
directions: In the center of a tortilla, spread some refried beans. Sprinkle some meat, onion and cheese.
Add some salsa and sour cream.
Tuck 2 sides in and gently roll up.
Serve at once.

title: big bill's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.

title: dirt delight
directions: Combine pudding with milk; set aside.
Cream the margarine with the cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar.
Combine with pudding; add Cool Whip.
Crush Oreos and place most in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add filling on top and the rest of the crushed Oreos.
Refrigerate to set.
Serve.
Best if sits overnight.

title: creamy onion and potato soup
directions: Melt butter in pan over low heat.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute; stir constantly.
Add onion and garlic. Cook 1 minute or until onion is tender.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes and next 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring constantly, or until done.

title: initial sourdough starter
directions: Pour water into bowl.
Sprinkle yeast on top.
Wait 5 minutes or until mixture is bubbly.
Gradually mix in flour.
Pour into clean jar and cover lightly.
Set in a warm place for 24 hours.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Beat in the eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually blend dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Place by dropping tsp. on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 350 for 10-12 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into large baking dish. Sprinkle herb stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° until real bubbly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Partly bake pie shell. Beat eggs very slightly.
Add sugar, syrup, vanilla, salt and pecans. Mix well.

title: marshmallow bars
directions: Heat marshmallows and margarine in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Stir in half of the cereal at a time until evenly coated.
Press into buttered baking dish, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Cool; cut into bars, 2 x 1-inch.
Yields about 3 dozen bars.

title: crunchy crust pound cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan with butter.
Make sure to coat evenly, ridges and center tube with almonds.
Beat remaining butter with sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Beat in vanilla and orange rind.
Stir in flour, then beat until batter is smooth.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Put in casserole, mix together.
Mix noodles with 1 cup broth. Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash and
half bell peppers, removing seeds.
Mix beef, rice, onion,
salt
and pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce. Stuff peppers with
mixture.
Pour
remaining
sauce
over peppers. Cover and bake in oblong baking
dish
at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove and cover top of each pepper with cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all the sauces, preserves and sugar profusely and put in crock-pot on medium high.
Mix hamburger with diced onions and two raw eggs.
Throw in a handful of crackers and roll into balls.
Fry in skillet until done.
Then drop into a crock-pot.
Cook for 45 minutes on high, then for 15 minutes more on low.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine tuna, bread crumbs, celery and onion.
