Blend mayonnaise, chili sauce and lemon juice.
Stir into tuna mixture. Form into 4 patties.
Fry in lightly oiled skillet over medium heat for about 5 minutes or until nicely browned.
Serve on buns with lettuce and tomato slices.
Serves 4.

title: chili-cheese bake
directions: Combine the Cheddar cheese and Jack cheese.
Sprinkle 1/4 of the cheese in the bottom of a greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Top evenly with 1/3 of the chilies.
Repeat layers 2 more times; then top with remaining cheese.
Beat eggs; beat in milk and pour over chilies and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center appears firm when dish is jiggled. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
You may add additional milk to bring to about 2 inches from top if needed. Freeze in ice cream freezer, cranking until real solid or stiff.
Remove paddle and pack with plenty of ice cream salt and crushed ice.
Cover and let stand for several hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and bake in a shallow casserole at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 12.

title: poppy seed lemon bread
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl; blend for 4 minutes. Pour into 1 large or 4 small loaf pans. Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes for large pan (start testing at 45 minutes to avoid overcooking); 40 to 45 minutes for small pans, checking doneness at 30 minutes. Can be baked in cake pans; adjust cooking time.

title: holiday cranberry coconut cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed until smooth, then at high speed for 3 minutes.
Fold in cranberries, pecans and coconut.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Check with wooden pick.
Place on wire rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to first mixture and mix well. Stir in nuts, dates and candied fruit. Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° to 375° until brown, about 10 minutes.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Chop cranberries; mix with water, sugar, flour, nutmeg and lemon rind.
Fill pie pastry with mixture.
Dot with butter, cut into small pieces.
Top with whole layer of pie crust or crisscross strips, your choice.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Great to top off a dinner of fish, fowl, pork or beef.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Brown ground beef.
Add vinegar, brown sugar, catsup, mustard, celery, water and the browned onions.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to box recipe.
Cook in round pans.
When done, put in a bowl and make holes with fork.
Put sugar to taste over strawberries and let stand to form liquid. Pour over cake in bowl.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: meatball hoagies
directions: Mix ground beef, parsley, bread crumbs, milk, eggs and cheese in bowl until well-blended.
In a large skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil over medium heat until lightly browned.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl with the beaten eggs. Bake at 400° in a large baking pan until bread is good and brown.

title: spaghetti or pizza sauce
directions: Let juice set and pour off top and use thick juice.

title: bundled fish on the grill
directions: Cut fillets into serving size portions.
Cut six pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil, 12 x 12 inches each.
Grease lightly.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth; cook and stir constantly until mixture boils. Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and set to the side.
Brown meat in a skillet with oil; season to taste.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin with 2 tablespoons cold water.
Add salt and sugar.
Stir in the cranberries, orange juice, lemon juice and rind, nuts and cinnamon.
Stir well.
Pour into mold. Refrigerate; chill well before removing from mold and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
In medium bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl cream butter, sugar
and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add
dry ingredients
until
blended.
Stir
in
semi-sweet chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop by well-rounded teaspoonful or
ounce scoop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool cookies on rack.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Spread on tortilla and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place in container with seam side up. Chill for at least 2 hours and slice to serve.
Can be served with salsa.

title: jon's holiday ham
directions: Preheat oven
to
Score and dot ham with cloves. Put all ingredients
in a mixing bowl and mix.	Pour over ham. Bake in covered
roasting pan for 2 hours.	After 2 hours, add mixture of 1 pound of brown sugar and 1 large jar of horseradish mustard. This
is
the
glaze.
Pour
over
ham and cook, uncovered, for 1/2
to
1 hour.
Baste every 15 minutes.
Use liquid as gravy. May want to thicken with cornstarch.

title: corn and black bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine corn, beans, onion, pepper, tomato and garlic.
In a
jar, combine Italian dressing, Tabasco sauce, chili, cumin, vinegar and cilantro. Cover and shake well. Pour over vegetables.
Chill at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and add dressing, cheese and bacon just before serving.

title: kara's chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken and shred with fingers. Cook noodles in broth from chicken. Drain off excess liquid after noodles are cooked. Place noodles, chicken, soup, peas, mushrooms and sour cream in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° until hot, 30-45 minutes. Light or non-fat soup and sour cream can be used.

title: green rice
directions: Place rice in greased baking dish.
Beat the egg and add the other ingredients; pour over rice.
Cover to cook.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Arrange in buttered 3-quart dish. Combine cream cheese and milk to make a smooth paste.
Add salt, garlic salt and half the Parmesan to cream cheese paste.
Stir over medium heat until smooth.
Pour about 1 cup sauce over the broccoli.
Place chicken slices over sauce.
Top with remainder of sauce.
Sprinkle with remainder of Parmesan.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Add onion rings on top for the last 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Add peppers, onion and celery. Fry until tender.
Add mushroom soup, cheeses, cooked rice and broccoli.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered.
Uncover and bake an additional 5 or 10 minutes.

title: stuffed pork tenderloin in onion sauce
directions: Split tenderloins lengthwise, but not quite through.
Pound to flatten slightly.
Saute vegetables in oil.
Remove from pan. Reserve 1/2 cup vegetables.
Stir crumbs.
Salt and pepper remaining ingredients.
Spread over meat.
Fold cut sides together and fasten with string.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve
jello in 10 ounces of hot water; set aside to cool (do
not
let set).
Mix
two cups of crumbs with melted margarine.
Press
into
bottom
of pan (12 x 15-inch).
Allow cream
cheese to soften at room temperature; cream with sugar. Whip
evaporated
milk
(must
be chilled).
Add cream cheese, sugar,
pineapple
and jello; beat all ingredients thoroughly. Pour into pan on crumbs.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Refrigerate two hours before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread cubes in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Mix together remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour over bread cubes.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.
Serve warm. Makes 6 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer coconut, then pecans in the bottom of the pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on the box; pour into pan.
Beat the last 4 ingredients until creamy and drop by spoonfuls carefully over the cake batter. Bake 45 to 50 minutes and remove.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Blend cheese, salmon, lemon juice, onion, horseradish and liquid smoke (may add more smoke after tasting).
Sprinkle chopped nuts and parsley on ball if desired.
Serve with rye cocktail bread or crackers.

title: southern pecan fudge
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, butter, cocoa, milk, vanilla and salt.
Heat over low heat until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in buttered 9 x 5-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown ground meat and drain. Cook macaroni and cheese. Combine meat, corn, and macaroni and cheese. Pour into a casserole dish and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichokes and mash well with fork or mixer.
Mix with mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Spread in greased, small flat dish.
Bake 20 minutes until golden brown on top.
Serve warm with crackers.
For a crowd, you need to double the recipe.

title: brickle blond brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter or margarine. Add both sugars and cream well. Add eggs and vanilla, beat until fluffy. Blend in dry ingredients. Stir in brickle. Spread in well greased 13x9 baking pan. Bake at 350° until done (about 30 minutes). These can be frosted. I sprinkle with chocolate chips while warm from the oven.

title: homecoming potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes round in large baking pan.
Mix water and cream of mushroom in mixing bowl, then pour over potatoes, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 250° in oven 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix syrup and sugar well.
Stir in raw peanuts.
Place in microwave for 7 minutes.
Remove from microwave; stir in butter. Return to microwave for 3 minutes.
Remove from microwave; add soda.
Stir and pour into pizza pan (sprayed with Pam).
Cool; break into pieces.

title: yum yum coffee cake
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.

Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together. Add dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Put half of the mixture in pan.
Cover with half of the nut mixture, then add remaining batter and filling.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: bologna salad spread
directions: Put in food processor chopped bologna, eggs and onion.
Add relish, salt, pepper and salad dressing.
Blend 1 minute.
Spread between slices of bread and serve with chips.

title: confetti rice(4 servings)
directions: In medium saucepan, cook rice according to package directions. Cool. Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 cups cooked rice for quick day.
Stir vegetables, butter and parsley into remaining rice; heat through.

title: roll out cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with an electric mixer.
Beat eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour, one cup at a time, mixing after each addition.
The dough will be very stiff.
Blend last flour in by hand.
Do not cut dough.
Divide dough into 2 balls.
Roll out on a floured surface until about 1/8-inch thick.
Dip cookie cutters in flour before each use.
Bake cookies for 6 to 7 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: brown rice and vegetable medley
directions: In 9-inch skillet heat oil over medium heat.
Add scallions and garlic; saute until softened.
Add mushrooms, zucchini and red pepper.
Saute until red pepper is tender-crisp, about 5 minutes. Add soy sauce and pepper and stir to combine, stirring often until mixture is heated through.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Roll into ball shape.
Roll in bacon bits to cover.

title: sausage smorgasbord
directions: Prepare Salami Wedges and Sausage Frills.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: angel bars
directions: Mix with spoon and pour into ungreased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut stew beef into cubes, flour and brown on all sides in 6-quart Dutch oven in cooking oil.
Add seasoning, water and salt. Simmer for 2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook for 30 minutes on medium heat.

title: quick grape jelly
directions: Combine grape juice and sugar in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in pectin; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Quickly pour hot jelly into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids, screw on bands.
Process in boiling water 5 minutes. Yield: 4 half pints.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Set aside. Cube all vegetables. Cube Monterey Jack cheese. Crush Doritos in bag. In large salad bowl, combine all ingredients and toss while adding Ranch dressing. Serve immediately. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Cook first two ingredients together in a double boiler for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally.
May be necessary to add a little milk.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Vary by adding currants or raisins part-way through cooking period.

title: steak roll-ups
directions: Cook rice until tender; drain.
Stir in next 7 ingredients. Cut steak in 6 pieces.
Pound each to 6 x 4-inches.
Spread steaks with rice.
Roll up; fasten with picks.
Brown in hot fat.
Add soup and 1 cup of water.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat. Add water to pan drippings to make 1 cup.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup water.
Stir into liquid.
Cook and stir until thickened. Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Warm Cheez Whiz and soup together.
Place ingredients in casserole in order given (all raw).
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: wild rice and mushroom dressing
directions: Cook rices according to package directions.
Saute bacon until crisp; remove and crumble.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until soft and yellow.
Add remaining ingredients using enough chicken broth for a moist dressing.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serves 8.
Freezes well.
Excellent with turkey and ducks.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour and spices together.
Add sugar, Crisco oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 1 pound cans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Check.
May need to bake for 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Chop and cook the head of cabbage just crisp-tender.
Drain. To prepare cream sauce, melt margarine, stir in flour until smooth and add milk.
Cook over medium heat and stir until thick.
Saute green peppers and onion in oil until tender.
Place layer of cabbage in a lightly greased baking dish, sprinkle with sauteed onion and pepper, add grated cheese.
Cover with cream sauce and cracker crumbs.
Bake about 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: dill dip
directions: Place all in blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Chill, covered, at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with sweet pepper strips, zucchini sticks and other vegetables.
Makes enough for 8.

title: creamy potatoes
directions: Precook potatoes in microwave until slightly tender.
Spray skillet with vegetable spray.
Brown onion and potatoes.
When golden brown, add the rest of the ingredients and simmer until it thickens.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 275° for approximately 3 hours.
Turn pan upside down and let cool.
Cake will come out on its own.

title: mexican dip
directions: Line pie plate with cream cheese.
Pour in salsa and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: low-fat grilled tuna snack sandwiches
directions: Mix together tuna, relish, onion powder, Mrs. Dash and mayonnaise. Spray nonstick spray on skillet and heat on medium-high. Assemble sandwiches. In separate bowl, beat together egg substitute and milk. Dip each side of sandwich and toast on skillet. Serve hot. Cut into 4 squares or halves.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla until smooth. Whip the cream and fold into the first ingredients. Spoon gently into crust. May garnish with chocolate slivers, if desired. Chill well.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix well then spread on cake.

title: monterey chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and shred meat.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add soup and chopped green chilies and tomatoes to meat. Combine thoroughly.
Add sour cream to taste.
Put mixture in casserole dish.
Cover with tortilla chips and cover with cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves four people.

title: orange breakfast nog
directions: In a blender container, combine buttermilk, orange juice concentrate, brown sugar and vanilla.
Cover and blend until smooth.
With blender running, add ice cubes, one at a time, through opening in lid.
Blend until smooth and frothy.
Makes 2 (about 10 ounce) servings.

title: shipwreck
directions: Put 1 layer potato slices and 1 layer onion slices on bottom of baking dish.
Crumble hamburger over onions.
Sprinkle with rice, salt and pepper.
Pour kidney beans and tomato soup on top. Sprinkle with chili powder to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pimentos
directions: Boil 20 minutes and put in jars; seal.
Baby food jars with the rubber band inside are great for this.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
After cake has cooled, prepare pudding according to package directions.
Pull cake apart into chunks.
Alternate one layer of cake chunks with layer of strawberries, layer of pudding mix, layer of pineapple, then layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat each layer 2 more times.
Fills most small punch bowls.
Refrigerate.

title: holiday lime jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on box.
Chill until half jelled.
Add sour cream.
Beat with mixer until thoroughly mixed. Drain pineapple until all juice is drained.
Add pineapple to Jell-O and sour cream.
Mix. Add nuts; mix.
Garnish with split cherries.
Chill until set.

title: irish cream
directions: Add ingredients in order and stir. Put in jar or bottle and refrigerate.
Serve over ice, in coffee or straight.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook and stir green pepper and onion in oil until tender but not browned.
Add corn, salsa and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add cheese, if desired.
Fluff with fork.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, salt, Karo and water in saucepan, stirring until boiling.
In large mixing bowl beat egg whites until stiff.
Cook syrup until 248°, then pour 1/2 mixture into eggs while beating. Return to stove and cook until 272°.
Pour in mixture and mix. Add nuts and vanilla, stir with wooden spoon.
Drop with teaspoons as soon as mixture does not move.
Always have someone to help, as it must be done quickly.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Dissolve together all ingredients.
Cook on flame until it reaches the hard crack stage.
(This is where you pour into cold water and it solidifies in a stream.)
Pour over popcorn.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until peaks form (high speed).
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.

title: frozen slush
directions: Bring water and
sugar
to a boil, then add the juices. Freeze for at
least
12 hours.
When ready to serve, put some slush in a glass and pour 7-Up over it.

title: light temptation
directions: Prepare angel food cake mix as directed on box.
When cake has cooled completely, trim brown crust and remove from pan.
Cut cake into three layers using long, thin serrated knife.
Prepare whipped topping as package directs, using milk.
Stir in yogurt, one-half of the strawberries and the food coloring.
Spread one-third of the whipped topping between each layer and on top of the cake.
Top with remaining strawberries.
Before serving, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
tags: one-step Betty Crocker white angel food cake

title: bubble up pizza
directions: Quarter the biscuits and put into a bowl.
Add 1 cup sauce, 2 cups of cheese and any other toppings.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour the other 1/2 cup sauce over the top, then sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 20-30 minutes.

title: cheese ring
directions: Spray Pam on cake mold.
Mix all ingredients except preserves and place in mold.
Put the preserves in center.
Even up and chill. Add crackers.

title: pearl's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon and tomato sauce; put into loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips bacon.
Pour the tomato sauce over meat loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook for 20 minutes, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: southwest bake
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic until done; drain off fat. Add beans and corn; mix well.
Put in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese.
Mix cornbread as directed on package.
Pour on top of mix in baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° until cornbread is done.

title: sandy's easy chili
directions: Brown hamburger in oil with onion and bell pepper.
Add sauce, beans with liquid and tomatoes.
Add spice, then simmer about 45 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Take pit from avocado and save.
Blend all ingredients in blender; put avocado pit back in sauce (to retain green color). Especially good to dip raw vegetables in.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Place potato chips in plastic bag; crush chips. Dip chicken pieces in butter.
Roll in potato chips.
Place on a foil-lined baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until crispy.

title: apple pie
directions: Put apples in medium size saucepan.
Pour in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Stir well and cook for 15 minutes. Turn off gas while apples are cooking.
Make Basic Pie Crust.
Gently lay uncooked pie crust in bottom of 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bottom of pie crust with 1/2 tablespoon of cornstarch.
Pour in apples. Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.

Sprinkle again with 1/2 tablespoon cornstarch. Cover top with other rolled pie crust. Trim edge and seal. Slit center of pie crust. Prick around top with a fork. Brush top with beaten egg. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If edges start to turn brown, cover with tinfoil.

title: melted cheese delight
directions: Microwave:
Mix all together in a microwave-safe dish. Microwave until smooth and creamy, stirring after every minute.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in water until tender.
Drain.
Blanch with cold water and drain again.
Add seasoned salt, salt, eggs, celery, green peppers and pimentos.
Toss lightly.
Add English peas.
Toss lightly.
Gently mix in mayonnaise.
Chill several hours before serving.
Garnish as desired.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Cook chicken with enough water to cover it until tender. Then cool, skin and debone chicken and set aside. With broth from chicken and cans of broth, add everything but rice and chicken. Bring to a boil and cook 15 minutes. Add rice and chicken and cook 10 more minutes, then serve.

title: circle pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and eggs.
Add pecans, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked shell and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco, butter and eggs.
Add milk, vanilla and lemon alternately with flour and baking powder, beginning and ending with flour.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan (or use Pam spray) at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Using a 6 or 8-quart pot, saute the peppers and onions.
Add next 7 ingredients, stirring well after each addition.
Stir in baked beans; simmer for 1 hour.
Add Coke 15 minutes before beans are done.

title: grilled liver with port sofregit
directions: Process or mince bacon, garlic and olive oil.
Add chopped parsley, reserving 1 to 2 tablespoons for garnishing.
Pulse or chop to blend, set aside.
In shallow saucepan add beef stock and Port, bring to boil.
Reduce by two thirds, then remove from heat.

title: egg in orange shell(serves one)
directions: Cut orange in half.
Use one half; remove pulp and eat it. Remove and discard membrane.
(If desired, line shell with wax paper or bacon.)
Break egg in shell; season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Bake in a 325° oven or in the coals of outdoor fire.

title: bran muffins
directions: Grease bottoms of 12 muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Pour milk over cereal; let stand 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Fill each cup 1/2 to 3/4 full, depending on the size muffin that you want.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake muffins until golden brown and firm, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pork or chicken au gratin
directions: Spray ceramic casserole with nonstick spray.
Spread 1 can of soup on bottom of pan.
Place pork or chicken in a single layer on soup.
In separate bowl, mix other can of soup, potatoes, broccoli and 1 to 2 cans water until creamy.
Spread over meat and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: grillades(marinated steaks)
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces and season with salt and pepper.
Add steaks to hot oil in a heavy skillet to brown.
Do not turn over until you can see brown from sides.
Then turn over and brown other side.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Cover lightly and lower fire; simmer about 45 minutes or until tender.
Add hot sauce and serve over rice or grits.

title: malt-o-meal magic muffins
directions: Stir until flour is moistened.
Fill greased muffins cups 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Pour half of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Let jell. Spread sour cream over top.
Put in refrigerator 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour rest of mixture on top.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: grapefruit slush
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice and cool.
Add canned grapefruit that has been broken up into bite-size (or smaller) pieces.
Should be kind of mushy.
Place in freezer tray and stir once or twice while freezing.
Allow about 10 minutes before serving.

title: summer pilaf
directions: Heat butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add green onions, nuts and garlic; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until nuts are lightly browned.
Add rice, salt, pepper and thyme; cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes or until ingredients are blended.
Serve with kebabs. Makes 6 servings.

title: lighter pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Heat oven to 425°.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, ginger and salt in small bowl.
Beat egg whites lightly in large bowl.
Stir in pumpkin and sugar mixture. Gradually stir in evaporated milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, lower temperature to 350° and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: vegetable hot dish
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain. Place in casserole dish. Combine soups and milk. Pour over vegetables. Top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together.
(I use my electric mixer.) Mix the egg yolks, melted butter or oleo and milk together.
Blend into the dry mixture.
Do not overmix.
Fold in most gently, the beaten egg whites.
Cook according to manufacturer's directions. Makes 4 to 5 waffles.

title: ham noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles approximately 10 minutes. Drain and let cold water run over them.
Place alternate layers of noodles and ham in greased casserole to within 1-inch of top. Beat eggs with milk. Pour over noodles and ham.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave on High for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: kielbasy
directions: This is for 30 people, so you will have to cut down for the number of people you plan to serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip first 3 ingredients together until fluffy.
Fold in 2/3 of Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust, then top with the other 1/3 of Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in a small amount of oil.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together in a bowl.
Add vegetables.
Put in a casserole dish that has been lightly oiled.
Melt 1 cup margarine. Pour over 1 package of finely crushed Waverly crackers.
Put this topping on the vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° until heated through and beginning to bubble.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add flour and mix.
Spread 1/2 batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling on top.
Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken paella
directions: Heat oil in skillet and add onion, peppers, tomatoes and garlic; cook until onion is transparent.
Transfer to a casserole. Brown the chicken, add to casserole and season well.
Add the rice, chicken broth and turmeric to the casserole and stir gently.
Cover and bake for 35 minutes.
Uncover, add shrimp and peas, stir, return to oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until chicken is tender and rice is cooked.
Cook in oven at 350°.

title: 8 minute cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together until creamy, then add Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell or in small separate pie shells.
Cool 4 hours in refrigerator before serving. Top with cherry filling.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut dough into 1/8-inch slices. Line a 14-inch pizza pan with slices, pressing to form a crust. Bake in oven at 375° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown. Let cool, then blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cookie crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese. Glaze with mixture of marmalade and water.
Chill. Makes 12 or more servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter.
Beat with mixer until fluffy. Stir in powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Shave a little of the chocolate or Hershey bar on top for decoration. Cover and place in freezer.
Remove from freezer about 45 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger chow mein(my son, david walmsley's, favorite meal)
directions: Brown beef and celery in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Sprinkle with dry soup mix and cornstarch over meat mixture; stir in.
Then add soy sauce, water and bean sprouts.
Mix all together.
Bring to boiling point.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Top with chow mein noodles.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup (undiluted), sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Crush cereal and stir in remaining butter. Sprinkle over potato mixture and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: hungarian nut rolls refrigeration dough
directions: Have butter at room temperature and beat until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs, cream, vanilla and yeast.
Gradually add flour.
When dough is too heavy to beat with spoon, mix by hand until very smooth.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to use, cut dough in 5 sections.

title: valentine day kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine margarine, powdered sugar, cherry juice, almond extract and food coloring. Blend well.
Add flour, salt and cherries and mix well.
Form dough into 1 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 48.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Combine tomato soup and cream cheese and cook until smooth. Add the gelatin.
Mix well the remaining ingredients and add to gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold and chill.
Serve with fancy crackers.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Soak ground squash and onions in salt overnight; next morning drain in sieve.
Wash by running water over mixture while still in sieve.
Drain very well.
Place in large cooker.
Mix all ingredients well and simmer 35 minutes.
Seal in jars.
Process for 30 minutes in a boiling water bath for pints.

title: farina dumplings(for soup)
directions: Bring milk and salt to a rolling boil.
Briskly stir in the farina. Continue to stir until batter comes loose from sides of pot.
Remove from heat.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Add parsley. Bring broth to rolling boil. With tablespoon, cut the mixture and immerse into the boiling broth. Reduce heat.
Slowly cook the dumplings for about 15 minutes, partly covered.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese; add 1 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put over crumbs.
Mix jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Set aside until thick, then spread over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle top with pretzel crumbs.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute meat and sausage in oil.
Then add to sauce (tomato puree, garlic, salt and pepper).
Cook on low-light for 2 to 3 hours.
Cook lasagna according to directions on box.
Mix the Ricotta and eggs.
Shred Mozzarella.
In a deep 12 to 13-inch lasagna pan, add sauce, then lasagna, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves six to eight.

title: bachelor button cookies
directions: Combine.
Cookie batter will be very stiff.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian burger
directions: Cook hamburger until done. Brown pineapple on both sides. Serve on buns.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add kidney beans, chili powder, water, tomato paste, tomato sauce and parsley in a large saucepan.
Mix well.
Add in ground beef and mix well until thick.
Put in a large casserole dish.
On top of that put cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
(Before putting in casserole dish, mix in Fritos.)

title: savory pot roast
directions: Brown meat on all sides in small amount of oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion.
Mix all other ingredients except potatoes and carrots and add to roast.
Cover and cook slowly for about 2 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots the last 45 minutes of cooking time.

title: margie's lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar together; press this mixture into a small baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into hot crust; bake again at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle on top with powdered sugar and serve.

title: santa fe white chili
directions: Combine garlic powder, cumin and oregano in small dish and blend; set aside.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over med-high heat.
Add chicken and onion; cook4 - 5 minutes or until chicken is lightly browned. Stir in chicken broth, chiles, mixed spices and bay leaf.

title: green bean casserole deluxe
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Squeeze fresh lemon juice over the cooked mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 can onion rings, in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese on top.
Crumble the rest of the onion rings on top and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cheesy zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini squash in cubes; cook in boiling water 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain and place in a casserole dish.
Set aside. Combine next 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir about 1/4 mixture into egg yolk.
Add to remaining hot mixture. Fry bacon crisp; break in small pieces.
Stir in bacon and chives in mixture.
Pour over squash.
Combine bread crumbs and oleo; mix well.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage omelet
directions: Place bread cubes in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs; add milk and seasoning.
Pour over bread.
Mix in sausage; sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight. Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes (if using Pyrex bake in 325° oven), uncovered.

title: creamed chicken and biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease the bottom and sides of a 11 X 7 inch baking dish.
Chop onion.
Heat butter in a nonstick skillet over medium high heat until melted.
Stir in onion.
Saute until tender.
Combine chicken, soup, sour cream, milk, and pimento in a medium bowl and mix well.
Spoon mixture into prepared baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle baked layer with 3/4 cup of cheddar.
Arrange biscuits in a single layer over top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheddar.
Bake until biscuits are golden brown and the sauce is bubbly, usually about 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: cranberry orange nut bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with orange juice.
Fold in cranberries, orange rind and nuts. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool in pans on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
When cool, wrap well.
Will keep for weeks in refrigerator.

title: christmas coffee
directions: Combine coffee, chocolate, sugar, cinnamon, cloves and anise in a crock or heavy pot.
Cover and cook on very low heat or as long as three hours.
Remove cloves and serve with spoonful of whipped cream and some chocolate shaving.

title: broccoli and cavatelli
directions: Cook cavatelli and broccoli according to package directions. (Do not overcook.)
Mix cavatelli, broccoli and butter.
Mix in cheese (reserve a little).
Put mixture in buttered casserole. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemony carrots
directions: Combine lemon juice, honey and water in a saucepan.
Add carrots and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Drain carrots.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with mint.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: imitation crab salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Slice crab meat and scallions and unthaw peas. Mix all the ingredients together and stir until well mixed. Chill for 2
hours or overnight.

title: chocochip marshmallow pie
directions: Combine marshmallows, milk and salt in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, just until marshmallows are melted. Chill until partially set.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil.
Add salt, chili powder and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Bring to a boil, tomatoes, corn and bouillon.
Add to skillet mixture.
Before serving, stir in green pepper and uncooked rice.
Let simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: breakfast brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown.
Drain well.
Line bottom of buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing perforation to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.

title: martha washington balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator for one hour. Roll in balls about size of a walnut.
With a toothpick, dip in melted 6 ounces chocolate chips and 1/2 block wax.
Drop on wax paper.

title: blueberry muffins(sugar-free)
directions: Toss blueberries with 1/4 cup flour until well coated.
Cream margarine and Sweet 'N Low; add egg.
Mix flour and baking powder. Combine the 2 mixtures alternately with the milk.
Add coated berries last.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: squash bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Stir in strawberries and stir it until all melted.
Cool for a few minutes while mashing bananas. Add pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serves 12.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into frying pan with hot oil.
Brown on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Batter will keep one week in refrigerator.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies.
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by teaspoon on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for about 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In large kettle, combine Jell-O with boiling water, stirring until Jell-O is dissolved.
Then fold all at once, strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and walnuts.
Turn 1/2 mixture into 2 (12 x 9 x 2-inch) pans.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours.
Spread each evenly with sour cream.
Gently spoon on the rest of the Jell-O mixture; refrigerate.
Cut into squares and serve.
Party size.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer first 3 ingredients for 1 hour.
Do not boil.
Let stand, covered, for 12 hours.
Add vanilla and vodka.

title: low-fat carrot salad
directions: Mix together carrot and apple.
Squeeze the lemon juice over this and toss.
Add dates and raisins and toss again.
Stir in yogurt, Miracle Whip and dill.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: graham finale cherry pie
directions: Brush bottom and sides of pie crust with egg yolk.
Place on baking sheet; bake in 400° oven 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Spoon pie filling into prepared crust.
In bowl, stir together flour, sugar and cinnamon.
With pastry blender or two knives, cut in mayonnaise until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over pie filing.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown.

title: fruit-scented play dough
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, salt and alum (or cream of tartar). In small bowl, combine boiling water, jello, oil and food color (if desired).
Add to flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Cool to room temperature; knead thoroughly on lightly floured surface until dough is smooth.
Store in airtight container.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat liquid from can of pineapple to boiling point.
Pour over Jell-O, stirring constantly, until dissolved.
Mash cream cheese and pineapple together, then mix.
Let set until partly congealed. Beat whipping cream, fold into Jell-O and add nuts and pimento.

title: easy icing
directions: Mix sugar and shortening well.
Add hot milk, a little at a time, beating with mixer.
Scrape sides of bowl often.
When all of the milk has been added, beat until light and fluffy.
Add flavoring of choice and food coloring, if desired.
Beat well.

title: sweet 'n' sour pork with chinese-style vegetables
directions: Thinly slice pork or turkey into bite size strips, then set aside.
Preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat.
Meanwhile, for sauce, stir together teriyaki sauce and cornstarch in a bowl. Stir seasoning packet from frozen vegetables into mixture.
Set sauce aside.

title: outstanding oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 3 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: easy christmas salad
directions: Combine and mix well.
Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan or individual molds.
Let thaw at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: mom's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in cool water.
Stir and set aside.
Pour boiling water over shortening and stir until creamy.
Add sugar, salt and cold water.
Stir and let cool.
Beat in the eggs.
Add yeast and stir.
Add flour and knead.
Let rise until doubled and shape into rolls or buns and let rise again.
Or you can refrigerate until used.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serving size depends on what you do with mixture.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart casserole dish. Microwave for 5 minutes on High.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Stir; microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes more. Stir in butter, vanilla and soda until light and foamy.
Work fast.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness on large, well buttered cookie sheet.

title: stuffed mushroom cups
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes, then in broiler 3 to 5 minutes.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° in glass dish).
Microwave chocolate and margarine in a large bowl on High for 2 minutes until completely melted.
Stir in sugar; blend well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts until blended.
Spread on greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Combine salt, sugar, mustard, vinegar and oil. Add remaining ingredients and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy; add next 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pie shell; pour filling over pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 35 more minutes.
Outer edge of filling should be set; the center will be soft or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients and store in the refrigerator.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Beat egg well, then add all the rest of the ingredients in bowl and mix.
Pour into greased bread pan.

title: pot roast(student favorite)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut a pocket in the roast so that it can be seasoned in the center.
Cover roast inside and out with vinegar for tenderness.
Season roast well with Creole seasoning and salt.
Stuff roast with chopped seasoned onions and pour the rest of the chopped onions around the roast.
Heat oil and roast on stove top for just a few minutes to brown all sides.
Add 1 cup water and Kitchen Bouquet.
Cover and bake for 3 hours, checking every 30 minutes or so and covering with juices.
Roast should stay very moist because of the onions, but if needed, a little water can be added.
Add chopped seasoned carrots and cook for another hour.
Add chopped seasoned potatoes and cook until tender.
Roast should be baked until it separates with a fork.

title: noodles
directions: Put flour in bowl; break egg and add salt and water.
Work to a stiff dough.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut in strips and put in hot broth.
Cook 15 minutes.
Fold cream of chicken soup in.

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Hollow out the center of a round Hawaiian bread and pour dip in the hollow.
Place pieces of bread around the loaf of bread and dip.

title: filled jumbo drops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Drop with teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Place 1/2 tsp. filling on dough, cover with 1/2 tsp. dough.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen. Store between layers of wax paper.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add onion, well beaten egg and buttermilk.
Drop by the spoonful into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh sweet potato salad
directions: For salad dressing: Mix sour cream, mayo, honey, lemon juice, lemon zest, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
For the salad, shred the sweet potatoes to yield about 4 cups. Chop the apple to yield about 1 cup.
Combine sweet potatoes, apple, raisins, pineapple and pecans in a large bowl and mix well.
Add salad dressing to sweet potato mixture and mix well. Chill, covered, for 2 hours or longer.
Spoon into a serving dish.
Serve cold.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given except cottage cheese. Pour 1/2 of mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cottage cheese on top.
Put other half of mixture on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked potatoes, tomatoes and onions
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil and butter.
Add tomatoes, parsley, basil, oregano and salt and pepper to taste to make sauce.
In a greased 3 1/2-quart casserole, layer sauce, potatoes and cheese.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: sweet potato-apple casserole
directions: In a pot with a tight-fitting lid, steam sweet potatoes in 1/2 cup water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Peel and slice them lengthwise in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Layer them in a casserole. Peel and core apples, slicing them 1/2-inch thick.
Lay apple slices on top of sweet potatoes.

title: oriental marinade
directions: Mix well.
Marinate beef or pork for 4 hours, chicken for 2 hours.
Barbecue meat: teriyaki-style beef, whole boneless pork chops, whole boneless chicken breasts or chunks.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a large saucepan, combine butter and flour, stirring well. Add milk, starting with 2 cups. When warm, start adding American cheese, slice by slice, using a whisk. Add enough milk to make mixture thin consistency.
Sprinkle in Parmesan or Romano cheese and black pepper.
Place cooked macaroni in pan.
Pour milk/cheese mixture over, completely covering macaroni. Add more milk, if needed.
Place 6 slices of reserved cheese on top of casserole, overlapping. Bake in a 350° oven in a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam until light brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix butter in milk and sugar in flour.
Combine mixtures. Separate eggs and add beaten eggs to mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Let cool.
Pour mixture into 10-inch pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add powdered sugar.
Put on top of pie and brown in a 450° oven.
This pudding mixture can also be used to make lemon cream pie.

title: blender brunch pie
directions: Blend first four ingredients in a blender or food processor for 2 minutes.
Fry and crumble sausage; drain well.
Mix sausage into blended mixture.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: wild rice soup ("sandy's")
directions: Cook wild rice in salted water about 35 or 40 minutes.
Saute leeks and mushrooms in butter; add flour.
Heat chicken stock. Add leeks, mushrooms and roux, stirring occasionally, until flour cooks.
Add rice, the half and half, sherry, salt and pepper. (Optional, add cooked turkey sausage.)

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Boil chicken in 2 cans broth with garlic, bay leaves and other seasonings.
Add water to fill pot; simmer for a while.
Cool and debone chicken.
Cook sliced carrots and celery in broth until almost tender.
Add onion, egg noodles, zucchini and cabbage. Cook on moderate heat until noodles are cooked.
Put deboned chicken back in pot and stir.
Add chicken bouillon or 3 to 4 Weight Watchers broth packets if you prefer a more flavorful broth and you aren't watching your salt intake.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in glass jar.
Use 2 teaspoonfuls in a cup of hot water.
Sweeten to taste.

title: grandma's best meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sauce.
Make meatballs about the size of a ping pong ball.
Bake in oven at 350° until done, around 20 minutes.
Use a spoon with holes to remove the meatballs from the pan and place on plate with two paper towels to drain off all the grease.
Heat the marinara sauce until it starts to boil then turn it down to a simmer.
Place the meat balls in the sauce and simmer for 45 minutes.
It makes about 10 meat balls. The sauce and meat balls can go over pasta or have meat balls with sauce and Italian bread.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil, cocoa and sugar.
Blend one egg at a time.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill all ingredients in refrigerator for 8 hours or overnight.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch bits and peanut butter over low heat in heavy saucepan.
Stir in corn flakes; mix well.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: texas millionaire cake
directions: Bring to boil the margarine, cocoa and 1 cup water.
In mixing bowl combine the flour, eggs, water, milk, vanilla and baking soda.
Mix
well.
Add boiled mixture; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hot cheese pie
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch greased metal baking pan with chopped peppers.
Sprinkle on cheese, then drizzle egg mixture onto cheese.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: potatoes and cucumbers
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, add potatoes, basil leaves, bay leaves, tomato and bacon. Season lightly to taste with salt and pepper. Add water.
Cover and cook on high heat.
When water boils, turn heat to low.
Keep water bubbling.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes more. Pierce potatoes with fork to check if tender and done. Season cucumbers to taste with salt, then chill.
Serve potatoes hot in shallow bowls with 3 chilled slices of cucumber on each serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: super moist carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix the remaining ingredients together in separate bowl.
Add to dry ingredients.
Line 9-inch pans with parchment paper.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Frost with your favorite cream cheese frosting.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Take out 1/4 cup of the mixture.
Roll out the rest of the dough on a cookie sheet.
Spread out the 1/2 cup peanut butter on rolled dough.
Spread evenly. Spread out all of the Marshmallow Creme on top of the peanut butter.
Sprinkle the rest of the mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut like brownies.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Mix soups and sour cream.
Stir into noodles and bite-size chicken pieces.
Pour into greased casserole dish and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Cook onions in butter until clear.
Do not brown.
Add celery, bell pepper, garlic, green onions and parsley.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are tender.

title: italian parmesan potatoes
directions: Heat grill. Cut 14-inch square sheet of heavy-duty foil. Place potatoes in center.
In small bowl, combine oil, Italian seasoning, salt, garlic powder and paprika.
Drizzle over potatoes.
Stir gently to coat. Wrap and seal securely with tight double folds.
Place foil packet on gas grill over medium heat or on charcoal grill 4 to 6-inches from medium-high coals.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Open packet.
Stir gently.
Sprinkle with cheese. Return to grill. Cook an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening, peanut butter and sugars. Add the egg and vanilla, then beat the mixture well.
Add the sifted dry ingredients and mix it thoroughly.
Chill the dough, then form it into small balls on a cookie sheet and flatten them with a fork, making a crisscross pattern.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: holiday frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze.

title: reese cup balls candy
directions: Mix by hand sugar, oleo, peanut butter and vanilla and roll into small balls.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter rocky road(microwave)
directions: In a large 2-quart glass bowl, combine chocolate and peanut butter.
Heat in microwave on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking time.
Stir until chocolate is melted and smooth.
Stir in peanuts and marshmallows. Immediately spread in foil-lined 11 x 7-inch baking pan. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into 35 pieces.
Keep refrigerated.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixer bowl or processor bowl.
Add oil, eggs and carrots and mix well.
Add nuts, raisins or pineapple, if desired.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan or two 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes and test.
Cool cake and frost.

title: crunch pound cake
directions: Mix and beat for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Put a very large pot of water on to boil in which to cook manicotti, adding several drops of olive oil.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Chop onion.
Drain olives.
Mix Ranch dip and sour cream.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: baby wipes
directions: Mix all together.
Cut thick paper towels (Bounty works well) into 1/2.
For mentioned portion, use 24 Bounty sheets, cut in half.
Pour 1/2 paper towels into a seal tight plastic container. Pour 1/2 of liquid over.
Repeat.

title: tuna hot dish
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine milk, soup, onion, pepper and cheese.
Cook in pan over low heat until cheese melts.
Add tuna and mix well.
Add mixture to macaroni.
Ready to serve.

title: sesame chicken and noodle salad(from first immigrant restaurant)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine chicken, noodles and remaining salad ingredients.
Toss with dressing. Refrigerate and let marinate 1 hour or longer before serving.

title: crawfish pasta
directions: Melt butter; add green onion, yellow onion and bell pepper and cook just until tender.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add crawfish tails and saute for 10 minutes.
Add half and half and cook until thick.
Cook noodles in separate pot.
Combine sauce and noodles and serve.

title: cranberry sherbet
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and cranberry juice.
Cool and freeze.

title: slick chick
directions: Place chicken in large bowl.
Pour Italian dressing over chicken.
Cover and let marinate several hours or overnight. Drain and roll in Parmesan cheese; place in single layer, skin side up, on baking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pecan drop cookies
directions: Add pecans to egg mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Should be light brown when done.
Makes about 30.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Shred carrot.
Combine eggs, sugar, vinegar, salt and butter.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
When cold, add 1/2 cup Carnation cream.
Pour over cabbage.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa in saucepan. Add beaten egg yolks, milk and vanilla. Mix well. Add butter. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Pour into shells. Beat egg whites with sugar until egg whites form peaks. Spread over chocolate mixture. Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes or until browned and set.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling, salted water for 20 minutes; drain.
Combine meat, 1/2 teaspoon salt and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well. Shape into
6 thin patties.
Brown in skillet.
Remove patties.
Drain off fat.
In skillet, melt margarine or butter. Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender, but not brown. Blend in flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except the bananas. Refrigerate overnight to chill. Add bananas and mix well to serve.

title: reba's florida chowder
directions: Brown meat slightly in skillet.
Pour off fat.
In another skillet cook potatoes, carrots, celery and onions.
Cook for 10 minutes with not too much water.
Season meat with garlic salt and onion salt.
Add veggies; cooking water and all.
Add Cheddar cheese soup.

title: inez ratatouille(eggplant)
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, over medium-low heat, heat oil. Add garlic, onions and green peppers. Cook, uncovered.

Stir occasionally until lightly brown (10 to 15 minutes). Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, stirring now and then, until eggplant is tender but holds its shape and only a small amount of liquid is left in pan.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: butter pecan ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted butter over. Mix and pat down as crust.
Whip together pudding, milk and ice cream.
Pour over crust and frost with Cool Whip.
Let set for at least 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening;
add eggs and blend together. Sift dry ingredients together, then add to first mixture. Add vanilla
and
nuts	last.
Pour
into
a
well-greased and floured pan.
Bake	40
to	45
minutes at 300°.
When cake is done, pour 1
small
bag marshmallows over top and put in oven until they begin to melt.

title: easy red beans and rice
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Place
large
size
x 20-inch) Reynolds
oven
cooking bag in a 13 x 9-inch pan; add flour to bag,
twist
end
and
shake bag to coat.
Add next 7 ingredients; squeeze bag to blend.
Add red beans and sausage; turn bag to blend ingredients.
Arrange ingredients in an even layer.
Close
bag
with
nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes until rice is done.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13 baking dish, add these ingredients in layers. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: corny dog recipe
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl.
Dip cooked and cooled hot dogs in batter.
Cook in deep hot grease until brown.
If there is any leftover batter, drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into hot grease.
This will make great "corn balls."

title: cheese sauce
directions: Cook onion in melted butter.
Mix in flour.
Add Parmesan cheese and salt, then add milk.
Beat egg yolks and put in cheese mixture.
Cook slowly 10 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese and mix well.
Cook one package lasagne noodles and layer with meat sauce in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
After final meat layer, seal top with cheese sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil, stirring well.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin.
Combine next 7 ingredients; add to pumpkin mixture alternately with water, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Spoon batter into 2 lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Serve with cream cheese and peach preserves if desired.

title: peanut butter playing dough
directions: Mix ingredients together, using varying amounts of dry milk for desired consistencies.
Knead it with fingers, forming into desired shapes and adding other foods like M&M's or peanuts for eyes, mouths, etc.
Great fun!

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix stuffing with 1/2 cup warm melted butter.
Add chopped clams, clam juice and minced crab meat; then add 2 tablespoons fresh minced garlic and green onions.
Melt remaining butter in a baking dish.
Take the mushroom caps and stuff with teaspoon (heaping full) and arrange in heavily buttered baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until slightly brown, then turn oven to broil until tops are crispy (about 3 minutes).

title: shrimp balls
directions: Chill shrimp, then mash very fine with fork or blender.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Roll lightly in finely chopped parsley.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Heat water.
Add in order powdered milk, coffee creamer, sugar and chocolate mix.
Serves 70 to 75 cups (for large groups).

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain the canned fruit.
Do NOT use any of the juice.
Place fruit in a large mixing bowl.
Over fruit, sprinkle pudding mix. Mix well, then add package of frozen strawberries.	Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: quick lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, condensed milk and Cool Whip and pour into pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: no-crust coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In the eggs, beat in sugar and margarine until smooth.
Blend in flour, milk, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients; drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12.
Note:
Fat Free, Sugar Free.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 3 qt. saucepan.
Bring to full boil stirring constantly.
Boil five minutes over medium heat, or until candy thermometer reaches 234 degrees with constant stirring to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients, mix until well-blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 or 13 x 9 pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares. Makes about 3 pounds of fudge.

title: tuna dip
directions: Break up tuna in a bowl.
Add softened cream cheese and 1/2 cup sour
cream.
Mix well, then add remaining ingredients and mix well again.
For
a larger group of people, double the recipe. Serve cold.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and put in greased square pan.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Mix together and sprinkle over top of batter.
Put in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: french dressing chicken
directions: Place chicken in long casserole dish and cover with French dressing topped with onion slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve over rice.

title: blueberry lovers' muffins(serves 12)
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and spices. Set aside.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix all except sesame seed.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Form small balls; roll in sesame seed.
Flatten on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Add together and beat until smooth and creamy.

title: easy homemade rolls
directions: Mix together and put in mini muffin tins.
Cook 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 30.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until crisp-tender.
Mix remaining ingredients except crumbs.
Add broccoli.
Place into greased casserole and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corned beef dinner
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Layer ingredients with macaroni in baking dish. Top with 3/4 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Garnish with parsley and olive slices. Serves 6 to 8.
Cook 1 hour at 375°.

title: russian tea
directions: This is to be used as hot toddy.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Blend with cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and cherry pie filling.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.

title: grilled salmon with fresh ginger
directions: Combine all ingredients to make a marinade sauce.
Rinse fillets under cold water and pat dry.
Place into a shallow dish in a single layer.
Pour marinade over fillets, turning to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate for 30 minutes.
Prepare grill and spray with Pam.
Grill salmon about 10 minutes per inch or until done. Brush with remaining marinade sauce.
Be sure to use fresh herbs.
Great on chicken, too.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream brown sugar, white sugar and shortening, then add eggs. Mix all the rest of ingredients together in large bowl. Drop on cookie sheet. Cook until brown.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot oil.
Pour combined remaining ingredients over chops.
Cover and bake at 325 for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Spread with butter.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring until crumbled and drain well.
Spoon over bread slices.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt.
Mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes or until set. Serves 8.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together.
Heat in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flavoring together.
Add flour, salt and figs; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add sour cream, flour, baking powder, soda and salt; mix well.
Mash 3/4 cup bananas and add to batter and chopped nuts.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 loaves in 5 x 3 x 2-inch pans.

title: hot dog snack wraps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut triangles in half lengthwise.
Place hot dog on shortest side of each triangle.
Place cheese on hot dog; roll up, starting at shortest side of triangle and rolling to opposite point.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with catsup and mustard.
Makes 32 snacks.

title: candy bar krispies
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together in pan and add about 6 cups of Rice Krispies.
Spread out in buttered pan.

title: the original kentucky hot brown
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add flour and stir to combine well.
Add milk in a slow stream, whisking constantly over medium heat.
Allow sauce to thicken, stirring often.
Add cheese and stir to melt.
Season to taste.
Place toast on heatproof platter. Top with turkey and cover each with 1/4 cup sauce.
Divide bacon and Parmesan cheese among sandwiches.
Broil until cheese has browned and sauce bubbles.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.
Good luncheon dish when served with hot rolls and a congealed salad.

title: chili con caso
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain off all fat.
Mix in remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Thin with evaporated milk. Serve with nacho chips.

title: tea punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together.
Steep tea bags in the sugar-water for 10 minutes.
Pour into gallon container.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Fill rest of container with water and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.

title: garbure basque(or ham and bean soup with vegetables)
directions: Place all ingredients, except frozen vegetables and cabbage, in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 12 to 18 hours.
Turn to high and remove ham.
Add peas, limas and cabbage.
Cook for 1 to 2 hours on high or until vegetables are tender.
Return ham to crock-pot for last 1/2 hour of cooking.
Serve bowls of the soup with crusty French bread.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs with fork. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: lo-cal pineapple pie
directions: Mix undrained pineapple and pudding mix together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pile into pie shell and chill.
Garnish with more Cool Whip if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter. Blend in lemon juice and seasonings. Heat gently; do not let butter brown. Broil cleaned shrimp about 5 minutes. Place on heated dishes and pour butter sauce over. Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage until the leaves separate.
Take ground beef and mix in onions and salt.
Add tomato sauce.
Take cabbage leaf and put a small ball of mixture and wrap.
Use toothpick to hold together.
Put cabbage rolls in casserole dish and pour whole tomatoes over cabbage rolls.
Cover with foil and cook at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Use your favorite yellow cake mix to prepare cake layers as you would for any other cake.

title: hormel ham n cheddar success
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Prepare mixed vegetables according to package directions, omitting margarine and salt.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Pour into pan; bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: apricot roll
directions: Add yeast to 3/4 cup warm water and mix until it dissolves. Add egg and beat until mixed.
Add hot roll mix, then work into a ball.
Put your ball into a bowl and let raise for 1/2 hour.
Take it out and work with it, then put it back in bowl and let it raise for 1 hour.
Roll into a rectangle and add apricot filling.
Roll like jelly roll.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix well.
Put on meat for several hours.
Stir occasionally. This marinade is great for rolled rump roasts or shish kabobs.

title: garbage candy
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cover with melted white chocolate.

title: potato supreme
directions: Cut onions in small pieces.
Fry bacon and set aside.
Cut and peel potatoes like for mashed potatoes.
Cook until done and drain.
Put sour cream, margarine and potatoes together and mash or whip good.
Add bacon (crushed), onions and drippings and stir salt and pepper to taste.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine. Spread 1/2 in bottom of large long
dish or pan.
Store in refrigerator while preparing filling.
Whip
envelopes of Dream Whip with milk. Add sugar
and
creamed cheese.
Beat until stiff. Spread
1/2 the filling
on
cracker
crumbs.
Spread
cups cherry pie filling. Add remaining filling and top with remaining crumbs. Chill 2 to 4 hours.

title: corn souffle
directions: Blend margarine, eggs, milk, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add corn and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine in a saucepan the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in reserved liquid, vinegar and batter.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add beets; heat through.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: no wait rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cream butter with sugar and egg. Add together with yeast; add flour.
Mix well.
Put in airtight container.
Store in icebox.
Use as needed.
Cook in muffin tins or knead a little and roll and cut.

title: popcorn treat
directions: Mix popcorn and nuts.
Put other ingredients in a pan and boil to hard-ball stage or 10 minutes after boil.
Take off heat and add baking soda and vanilla; stir.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
WORK FAST!
Spread out on cookie sheets so it won't glob together.
Break up and put in a bowl.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add all ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in top of double boiler. Slowly stir in hot milk; cook over direct heat until mixture thickens.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into well beaten egg yolks; cook until thick.
Add the sliced bananas and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks.
Cover the cream mixture and brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in hot water to thaw.
Drain thoroughly and place in casserole dish.
Saute onion in oleo.
Pour over broccoli.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or spray with Pam.
Mix all ingredients and then spread in pan evenly.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Cut into squares.
Best to serve warm.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oleo.
Remove from the pan, brown meat and drain.
Stir in onion, garlic, soup, tomato sauce and paste, chiles and salt.
Cook until mixture begins to boil.
Place 3/4 of chips in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 10-inch pan.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Top with remaining chips and cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: cheddar specials
directions: Mix cheese and margarine together.
Add chips and flour.
Form into 1-inch round balls.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 50.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Crumble and brown meat; drain and cool.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread and mix well.
Add meat and cheese. Put in greased 8 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, butter, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Blend into first mixture.
Form 1-inch balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: puffy fried shrimp
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Beat egg slightly and milk.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Dip shrimp into batter, one at a time.
Fry in deep fat until brown. Drain on paper.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together and add egg yolks; beat. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift cake flour and regular flour. Add the flour and the buttermilk alternately to the sugar, butter and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Melt chocolate in boiling water; stir until chocolate is all melted, then add to cake mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
And lastly, add the egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
This makes 1 large cake or 2 squares.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Mix dressing by blending mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Combine broccoli florets, crumbled bacon, diced onion and raisins in mixing bowl and gently fold in the dressing. Serve salad slightly chilled.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Heat Jell-O, sugar, water and pie filling until warm, not quite boiling.
Remove from heat and add pineapple and Coke.
Put into jello mold or serving dish and chill until set.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into flat loaf and place into 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until well done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order except cheese.
Pour half of batter in a greased baking dish.
Add half of cheese.
Add remaining batter, cover with cheese.

title: quickie peanut butter bits
directions: Place butterscotch bits and peanut butter in large deep glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on 100% power 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring once.
Blend until smooth.
Pour cornflakes into bowl, blending lightly but thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie crust.
Then place 2nd pie crust on top.
Punch holes in top crust.
Cook at medium heat until done.

title: barbara's brownies
directions: Mix together together; bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: andy's snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt together and set aside.
