Beat butter, sugar (1 1/2 cups) and eggs together.
Gradually add the flour mixture until well mixed.

title: cheese things
directions: Have butter and cheese at room temperature. Mix all ingredients together. Roll in 1 inch balls and flatten with fork. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: country style steak and gravy
directions: Salt and pepper each side of meat.
Sprinkle each side generously with Morton Nature's Seasons.
Dip meat into flour and coat each side.
Pour small amount of vegetable oil into skillet, heating at 375°.
Add meat, browning on both sides.
Remove from pan.
Saute in oil one cut up large onion until lightly tender. Remove onion from pan and place with browned meat.

Add 2 tablespoons flour (from flour used for coating meat) to small amount of oil in hot skillet and brown, stirring constantly. Gradually pour water into browned flour, stirring until thickened. Add more water as necessary.
Add 1/2 teaspoon Kitchen Bouquet and stir.

title: rice casserole
directions: Pan #1:
Saute 1/2 stick margarine, mushrooms and oregano.

title: sour cream scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
In greased 3-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of ham, potatoes and onion with sour cream mixture.
Top with cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Beat Dream Whip and milk in mixer bowl until stiff. Add cream cheese and beat well. Add sugar and beat well. Pour half of this mixture into baked and cooled crust in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Spread all of the pie filling over this and cover with the remainder of the Dream Whip mixture.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pan.
Put bacon on top.
Cook at 350° for 1 to 2 hours or until almost dry.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in casserole dish in
layers. Sprinkle each layer with onion, salt and pepper.
Dot top with butter.
Pour hot milk on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 1/4 hours or
until tender.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place meat in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread soup over meat. Pour broth over all.
Dot butter over all.
Mix well the milk and flour.
Pour as evenly as possible over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sausage 'n' sauerkraut
directions: Cut the sausage into 1-inch slices; saute in a Dutch oven until fully cooked and browned; drain.
Add sauerkraut, tomatoes with liquid, celery, onion, green pepper, brown sugar and seasonings; mix well.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: pizza roll
directions: Roll bread dough out (after thawed) and place on cookie sheet. Warm
tomato sauce.
Add seasoning, if desired, such as Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Spread on bread dough.
Brown ground beef and spread over tomato sauce.
Spread chopped onion, pepperoni and cheese.
Roll dough around the ingredients.
Spread top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in a buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Spread beans in a serving platter.
Layer sour cream, salsa and guacamole.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Roll chops in flour and brown in fat.
Add 1 teaspoon catsup and 2 tablespoons sweet juice for each chop.
Place in slow oven for 30 minutes or until brown and well done.

title: brown sugar pies
directions: Melt butter.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: junk yard salad
directions: Mix well and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish or large bowl with cover and put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Keeps well several days.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sherried beef
directions: Place meat in large casserole or slow cooker with tight fitting cover (do not brown meat).
Heat mushroom soup, onion soup mix and sherry in a saucepan; do not add salt.
Pour over meat.
Cover casserole; bake in a 350° oven for 3 hours; cook in slow cooker for 3 to 3 1/2 hours at medium setting.
Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter or oleo with pretzels and sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 7 minutes or until brown.
Cool.

title: wheat and honey bread(in bread machine)
directions: In the order listed, put all ingredients into pan. Select white bread and push start.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil vegetables; drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Add cheese (cubed) and soup.
Cover with 1 roll of Ritz crackers and 1 stick of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snowball cake
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over boiling water; stir until all is dissolved.
Add sugar, pineapple and lemon juice; stir well. Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Prepare 2 packages of whipped topping as directed on package.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
In a large bowl, place layer of cake, then layer of gelatin until all is used.
Refrigerate until set.

title: colored squares
directions: Mix ingredients; cook until melted.
Add 1 package colored marshmallows.
Put in buttered pan.
Refrigerate.

title: tomato salad
directions: Place the tomatoes in a pan of boiling water for 2 minutes; drain and rinse with cold water.
Peel and thinly slice.
Place in a bowl with onion.
In a small bowl, mix remaining ingredients. Pour over the tomatoes.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Accompany with hot French rolls or Italian bread.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Cook apples and mash lightly. Add flour, sugar and salt. Beat egg and vanilla and add. Add sour cream with apples. Put in 9-inch pie shell, unbaked. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove and sprinkle with topping. Return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: pork roast with garlic and cracked pepper
directions: Rub garlic, salt and pepper on roast and put roast in small roasting pan with cover for 1/2 hour.
Add water and bake 3 to 4 hours at 325° (baste every hour) until roast is tender.
Slice; the broth makes a great gravy.
(I also do this in my crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on low.)
I also do round roast beef this way without garlic.

title: heavenly orange fluff salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice concentrate and fruits.
Mix well and pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish. Refrigerate until set.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cook onions and tomatoes together until done. Put in food processor. Add to butter and flour to which seasonings have been added. Cook together until thick.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill for 30 minutes.
A great dish!!
Serves 6.

title: spinach casserole 2
directions: Cook spinach until just tender.
Drain well.
While spinach is draining, saute onion in butter about 5 minutes.
Mix onion, soup, celery, spinach and a few whole croutons.
Put mixture in buttered casserole.
Top with crushed croutons.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook onion in butter in large skillet.
Blend in flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add broth.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Add remaining ingredients and heat together.
Pour into pastry lined tin.
Cover with top crust and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal fudge drops(no bake cookies)
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk. Boil for 1 minute rapidly.
Remove from stove, add vanilla, pinch of salt and peanut butter; stir.
Then add oatmeal last.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Heat almonds with sugar over low-heat in a heavy skillet, stirring constantly, until sugar is just melted and almonds are coated.
Cool and break apart.
Store at room temperature.
Combine vinegar, sugar, parsley, salt, pepper and vegetable oil in a screw-top jar.
Shake well to mix and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
Combine lettuces, celery, green onions and oranges. Toss with dressing.
Add almonds and toss gently.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel snappers
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
On it, arrange pecans, flat side down, in groups of 4.
Place 1 caramel on each cluster of pecans.
Heat slowly in oven at 325° until caramels soften, about 4 to 8 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Remove from oven with buttered spatula; flatten caramel over pecans.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan to wax paper.
Swirl melted chocolate on top.
Makes 36.

title: zucchini squash drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together the zucchini, soda, sugar, egg and the shortening.
In another bowl, sift together the flour, cinnamon, cloves and the salt.
Stir the sifted ingredients into the zucchini mixture.
When this is almost blended, add the raisins and nuts.

title: chocolate sundae dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs; press rest of crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze.
Slice ice cream in 1/2-inch slices; put on crumbs and freeze until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 cup margarine. Add powdered sugar and milk.
Cook until thick and creamy, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla; cool and spread over ice cream. Freeze until firm.
Spread whipped cream over chocolate layer and sprinkle with chopped nuts and reserved crumbs.
Store in freezer. Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes; drain off liquid.
Add salt, eggs and flour. Add grated onion, if desired.
Fry in well-greased pan.

title: tuna noodle skillet
directions: Combine tuna, 1/4 cup soup, cracker crumbs, onion, parsley, juice and egg.
Mix well.
Shape into 4 patties 1-inch thick. Brown in hot butter in skillet.
Remove from pan.
Combine remaining soup, sour cream and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in noodles, cheese and broccoli.
Arrange tuna patties over noodles. Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: failproof rice pilaf
directions: Use large 4 quart (no stick) pan which has been sprayed with oil on bottom and around sides.
Melt margarine and Crisco over high heat and add the Shirea cooking until golden brown stirring occasionally.
Add the rice and stir until all grains have been coated (approximately one minute).
Add the boiling water and stir. When water returns to rapid boil, put tight lid on pan, reduce heat to lowest setting and let steam for about 1/2 hour.
Lift lid, stir just one time, replace lid and let stand for another 15 minutes still on lowest heat.
Stir again and serve.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add cocoa and stir well.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add salt.
Add milk slowly.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Cool and store in a glass jar in refrigerator.
This will keep 2 to 3 weeks.
Serve over cake, ice cream and fruit.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add next four ingredients.
Layer with 6 corn tortillas.
Sprinkle with the cheese and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Put one wafer in bottom of each baking cup.
Mix first 4 ingredients with a mixer until creamy.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and put filling on top.
Chill before serving.
Makes 24 cupcakes.

title: sis and bill's favorite ratatouille
directions: Brown sausage; pour off fat.
Add onions, celery and green pepper and cook until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 2 hours.
Serve over elbows and top with Parmesan cheese. Freezes well.

title: peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat. Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.

title: potatoes and hamburger dinner
directions: Cook meat, bell pepper and onion.
Drain off fat.
Peel potatoes and cut in circles.
Cook until done.
Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover potatoes with meat mixture. Place cheese soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, covered with foil.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg and mix.
Add oil and mix.
Mix oatmeal, cornflakes, coconut and walnuts; add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Form the size of small walnuts.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake 12 minutes at 325°.
Cool on pan before removing.

title: chili with spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet until completely browned and onions are tender.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, beans and 2 cans of water.
Also add spices.
Stir well to mix all ingredients together.
Bring mixture to a simmer and cover with lid.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick brass cleaner
directions: Spray Scrub Free over brass, rinse with warm water and towel dry.
Work great for a quick touch up without the mess of brass cleaners!

title: ham and cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Spread cheese on each slice of ham.
Roll ham slices around a whole dill pickle. Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Slice.

title: scallops provencale
directions: Wash and dry the scallops and roll them in flour.
Heat the oil and butter together.
Add the scallops and cook them very quickly, tossing them lightly in hot fat so they brown delicately on all sides.
While they are cooking, add the chopped garlic and mix it in well.
Add salt and pepper to taste and just before removing the pan from the heat, add the parsley and toss until the scallops are covered with parsley.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Yields 4 servings.

title: quick baked beans
directions: In large skillet, saute onion in butter. Pour pork and beans into skillet. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil and then reduce to a simmer for 10 minutes.

title: christmas dinner vegetables
directions: Choose white turnips of uniform size (as many as you need for serving one per guest). Cook until tender. Scoop out centers, leaving a thin wall. Fill with tiny, diced and buttered beets.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Cook puddings in water until thick.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Cool.
Add drained oranges and fold in Cool Whip. Serves 8.

title: pineapple-pecan cheese ball
directions: Toast nuts in oven at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Chop 1 cup of nuts; set aside.
Grind remaining nuts.
In food processor or mixing bowl, combine ground nuts, cream cheese, pineapple, red pepper, onion and salt.
Process or beat until well blended. Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Shape in large ball or divide mixture and shape into balls.
Roll in
chopped nuts.
Wrap and chill until serving time or freeze.
To serve, thaw 24 hours in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers and/or fresh vegetables. Makes 3 cups.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onion.
Add rest of ingredients. Put in casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender. Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix in crushed cookies and press together for bottom layer. Place in refrigerator to cool.

title: cucumber raita
directions: Slice the cucumbers; sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt and let them sit for 15 minutes.
In another bowl, mix 10 ounces unflavored plain yogurt, 1/2 teaspoon sugar, 1/4 teaspoon cumin and the 1/2 medium sized onion.
Whip the yogurt mixture with a spoon.
Add the cucumbers and chill.
Garnish with 2 tablespoons finely chopped cilantro leaves.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zingerman's noodle kugel
directions: In a large saucepan, cook fettuccine according to package directions until just tender.
Drain and rinse under cold water. Drain and set aside.

title: meatball stew
directions: Cook potatoes while preparing other ingredients. Combine hamburger, mustard, chili powder, milk, egg, corn meal, salt and 3 tablespoons chopped onion. Mix well and form into meatballs. Roll in flour and brown in 3 tablespoons oil. Remove from oil and set aside. Thicken remaining fat in skillet with 2 tablespoons flour and add tomato soup or juice to make gravy. Add drained cubed potatoes and 1 cup chopped onion. Let simmer 1 minute. Add meatballs. Let simmer until done or layer in casserole dish and bake at 350° until done.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Remove from heat and fill unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes (until a crust appears on top).

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add cream, drained pineapple and bread cubes.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp stroganoff
directions: Melt butter, add shrimp and cook on medium for 5 minutes. Remove shrimp to warming pan.
Add rest of butter to pan.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Saute 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour on mixture in pan and mix.
Stir in broth and seasonings.
Reduce temperature and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Add shrimp. Serve over rice.

title: peppermint meringues
directions: Place one rack in the middle of the oven and second rack directly above.
Heat oven to 225°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil or baking parchment.
Beat egg whites in a large bowl until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat until soft peaks form. Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating 5 to 6 minutes until mixture is very smooth and glossy.
Spoon meringue mixture into 1 gallon size Ziploc bag.
Snip off corner to make 1-inch opening.
Squeeze mounds 1 1/2-inches in diameter and 1 1/2- inches high close together but not touching.
Sprinkle crushed candy canes on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Turn off oven; keep oven door slightly ajar and let cool approximately 1 hour. Remove from foil or parchment and store in airtight dry container up to 2 months.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Cook potato and mash until smooth.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
When heavy enough to knead, add vanilla.
Knead in the sugar.

title: joan burba's rice pudding
directions: Pour all ingredients into a greased baking dish.
Dot with more butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix the ingredients together, except for nuts.
Form into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped nuts or chopped parsley.

title: fruit salad
directions: Microwave cream cheese to melt.
Beat in milk; add fruit cocktail and mix.
Garnish with cherries and marshmallows.

title: wacky cake
directions: Measure flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in the sifter.
Put in 8 x 9-inch pan (ungreased).
Make 3 holes in pan with your finger.
Place vanilla in one, then oil and vinegar next. Pour 1 cup cold water; mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until light. Add beaten egg yolks and vinegar.
Add spices and raisins; mix well and fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. It forms its own meringue while cooking.

title: ambrosia salad(a holiday tradition)
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
Refrigerate	overnight or 24 hours. I usually double this when all our family is together.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Mix all together well and spread in a rectangular baking dish. Bake, uncovered. at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions.
Drain.
Return macaroni to pan and immediately stir contents of cheese packet into hot macaroni.
Blend well.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add raisins, nuts, chocolate chips, etc.
Fill 2 cookie tins, greased.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: rippin' zippin' kool-aid
directions: Place Kool-Aid into container.
Add sugar.
Squeeze lemon juice and orange juice.
Add pineapple juice and one cup of water. Add 5 ice cubes; stir.
Add enough water to make 2 quarts.
Add lemon, pineapple and orange slices.
Chill for 20 minutes.

title: pimento loaf bread
directions: Cut shortening into flour and stir in remaining ingredients. Put in one greased loaf pan.
Bake one hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Let set, covered in foil or wrapped
one day before cutting.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Lightly brown rice in the melted butter.
Add soup, water, mushrooms and water chestnuts. Bring to a boil.
Add almonds.
Pour into a covered 2-quart casserole.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not open while cooking. (This is very good with roast beef, pork or any kind of fowl.
If you like a one-dish meal, brown both sides of several pork chops and place on top of rice and bake for same time.)

title: venison pepper steak
directions: Slice venison into thin strips and brown in small amount of vegetable oil along with garlic.
Add onion and tomatoes and cook until tender.
Add 1 cup water with cornstarch and set aside.
Add soy sauce to broth and thicken with cornstarch mixture.
Add green pepper last and cook until slightly tender.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: honey fruit salad
directions: Core apples but leave a bit at the bottom for a plug.
Fill the holes with honey; sprinkle with a little grated lemon rind and cinnamon and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: egg toast
directions: Heat skillet or grill.
Make a hole in each slice of bread. Butter bread and holes.
Place in skillet.
Break eggs into the hole.
Cook until brown on one side.
Turn over and finish cooking on other side.
Place on plate.
Put small hole bread on top of egg.
Serve with strawberry preserves.

title: black and white fluff
directions: Chill prunes.
Remove pits, then cut into small pieces.
Slice bananas.
Cut marshmallows if using large ones.
Whip cream until stiff.
Add prunes, bananas, marshmallows, lemon extract and mix lightly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: In a heat-resistant, non metallic skillet, heat oil on a conventional surface until hot.
Sear pork chops on both sides until browned.
Sprinkle chops lightly with salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange onion and sauerkraut over pork chops.
Heat, covered, on simmer for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle caraway seed over sauerkraut and arrange apple slices on top.
Add water and heat, covered, on simmer for 10 minutes.
Heat, uncovered, on simmer for 10 minutes or until chops are tender.
Pork should always be cooked well done.

title: slumgullion
directions: Remove corn from cob.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet.
Add corn, tomato and hot pepper.
Cook 10 minutes or until done.
Add 1/4 cup water, if needed.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes, then 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: grampy saucy
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Bring	to a boil; boil slowly for
about	35
minutes.
This is a good barbecue sauce for chicken, beef or pork.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together, except egg roll shells. Separate egg roll shells.
Take the mixed ingredients and put in near the edge of the shell.
Fold opposite corners toward center, then roll shell, beginning at edge with mixed ingredients.
Deep fry in 350° oil.

title: walnut streusel muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine 2 cups of the flour and the sugar; cut in butter to form fine crumbs.
In small bowl, combine 3/4 cup of the crumbs and 1/4 cup of the walnuts; set aside.
Into remaining crumb mixture, stir the remaining 1 cup flour, the baking powder, spices, soda, salt and remaining 3/4 cup walnuts.
In another small bowl, combine buttermilk and eggs; stir into dry ingredients just to moisten.
Spoon into 18 greased or paper lined 2 3/4-inch muffin cups, filling about 2/3 full.
Top each with a generous spoonful of reserved crumb-nut mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until springy to the touch.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Loosen and remove from pans.
Serve warm.

title: corn and corn bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (until toothpick tests clear).

title: orange snow queen pudding
directions: In a glass serving dish pour orange juice over cake pieces; soak 1/2 hour.
Spread jam over top.
Place mandarin oranges on top of jam (save some to garnish).
Add pudding next, then whipped cream.
Garnish with oranges and almonds.

title: heart smart fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit. Mix pudding, milk, orange juice, and yogurt well. Add fruit and chill well.

title: crabbies(hors d'oeuvres that can be made ahead of time)
directions: Melt butter, cheese and mayonnaise; add salt to taste.
Mix in crab meat.
Spread on English muffin halves and cut into quarters. Place on cookie sheet and put into freezer until frozen.
After frozen, put into plastic bags and save until party.
When ready to use, place on cookie sheet and broil until brown and bubbly. Serve warm.

title: foolproof cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times, then add to eggs, oil and milk mixture.
Add
1 cup boiling water and vanilla.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture.
Add coconut cream pie filling or pudding mix.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans.
Makes 2 large loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in 9-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Double recipe for regular 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Ovens may vary baking time; don't overbake.

title: summer salad
directions: Boil pineapple 2 minutes.
Take off and add jello, then boil 2 more minutes.
Let cool then add cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Fold gently together in a bowl.
Keep refrigerated.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve in lettuce cups with a dash of paprika on top.

title: vegetable filling for egg rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill and fry egg rolls.
Serve with sauce.

title: california apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, and oil until foamy.
Add flour.
Mix together soda, cinnamon, salt, and pie filling.
Mix all together. Pour into a greased 9
X 13-inch pan.
Bake 350° 45 to 50 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole or hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and pour into ungreased casserole.
Spread the cornflakes and almonds on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chicken-almond bake
directions: Mix well.
Cover top with the crushed chips.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: linguine with sauce verde
directions: Process all ingredients, except pasta and almonds, in food processor or blender until well blended.
Cook pasta as directed on package; drain.
Pour sauce and almonds over pasta; toss to coat.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: diabetic pumpkin bars
directions: Cream margarine until fluffy.
Add brown sugar replacement, egg and water, beating until completely blended.
Beat in pumpkin puree; stir in flour and allspice.
Mix to completely blend. Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes or until sides pull away from pan.
Cool and cut into bars.
Yields 48 cookies.

title: juicy orange cake
directions: Mix according to package directions, then add Jell-O and bake as directed on box.

title: cantaloupe milk shake
directions: In a blender, place a few scoops of vanilla ice cream, some cut up cantaloupe and a splash of milk.
Blend together until thick and creamy.
Pour into tall glass and add a couple more pieces of cantaloupe.
Serve with a straw and spoon.
Mm mm - good!

title: raspberry or blackberry liqueur
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a 1-gallon, wide mouthed jar. Store in a cool, dark place.
Stir or shake every few days for about 3 weeks.
Strain through several layers of cheesecloth, reserving the liquid, but discarding the pulp and seeds. Refrigerated, the liqueur will keep indefinitely.
Makes 5 cups.

title: seviche
directions: In a glass casserole dish, mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
If spicier, increase hot peppers and Tabasco. May be served on crackers or in tart cups.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Using a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt the chocolate chips and sweetened condensed milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.

title: best ever cabbage soup
directions: In a large saucepan or stockpot, combine tomato juice and bouillon cubes and bring to a boil, stirring continuously until cubes are completely dissolved; lower heat to simmer and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage and carrots are tender.
Freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: carrots elite
directions: Slice carrots in 1/4-inch rounds.
Cook in just enough water to cover until tender.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup cooking liquid. Mix horseradish, onion, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Place carrots in 9-inch glass baking dish. Cover with mixture.
Mix bread crumbs and butter.
Spread over the top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: veggie snacks
directions: Spread the two cans of crescent roll dough flat on a cookie sheet.
Bake about 6 minutes until light brown at 400°.
Make a sauce of the cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and packet of Ranch dressing.
Blend together well.
Spread over the cooled crescent dough.
Finely chop all the vegetables.
Mix vegetables together and sprinkle on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: forever wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a pint of sympathy.
Flavor with a bright fireside and a loving kiss.
Bake well in warm arms all your life.

title: cheese bonbon
directions: Mix oleo and the cheeses together.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle
over
this,
mixing
well.
Roll pieces about the size of walnuts
with
your hands and press down the center of each with a
pecan	half.
Bake at 325° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip on the bottom of serving dish.
Scatter green onions on top of dip.
Mix sour cream, mayo and seasoning together.
Spread mixture on top of onions.
Spread cheese on the top.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook chopped meat with taco sauce mix according to package instructions.
In a 4-quart casserole dish, layer ingredients one at a time:
1/2 tortilla chips, 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 refried beans, 1/2 onion, 1/2 green pepper, 1/2 black olives, 1/2 salsa and top with 1/2 Cheddar.
Repeat another layer with remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° until cheese is melted and heated through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You may use Thank You cherry pie filling or other fruit. Alternate layers of bite-size pieces of cake, fruit, nuts and pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: halloween face paint(grease paint)
directions: Using rubber spatula, blend first 3 ingredients on a white plate to form smooth paste.
Add 3 or 4 drops glycerine for a creamy consistency.
The yield should be enough for a child's face.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown the meat; drain well.
Add cheese and Ro-Tel.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken without salt.
Cube.
Beat egg and blend in undiluted soups.
Add bread.
Cut into cubes.
Add cubed chicken. Pour into buttered casserole, 6 x 10 x 2-inch.
Top with cracker crumbs which have been stirred in melted butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: chili
directions: Chop onion and pepper finely, then cook with garlic until onion is soft.
Brown the ground beef; stir to break up meat. Drain grease.
Combine all ingredients in large pot and bring to a boil.
Cover pot, then simmer over low heat for 2 hours or more, stirring frequently.
Include chopped hot peppers for hot chili. Add water if chili gets too thick.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Use 1/3 cup mix to cup of boiling hot water.

title: kartoflane kluski(polish potato noodles)
directions: Stir all ingredients together until well mixed.
Dough will be soft and appear wet.
With the side of spoon that has been dipped in cold water, cut off approximately 1/4-inch portion of dough against side of bowl.
Working quickly, drop one portion at a time into four quarts salted, boiling water.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Drain in colander.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables, celery and onions all together, according to time on package.
Drain off water.
Mix cheese and mayonnaise together and add to vegetable mixture while hot, stirring until mixed well.
Add salt and pepper.
Melt butter, add Ritz crackers (crushed) and brown.
Put vegetable mix in casserole and top with cracker mix.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain the spinach, and distribute it evenly in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Mix together the soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese, and spoon over the spinach.
Top with crackers, pimientos and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes.

title: oatmeal crisp cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely and drop into a bowl of powdered sugar to dust.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix oil and sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Divide evenly in 3 pans and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on racks.
Cut each layer in half, so there are 6 layers.
Frost layers with Carrot Cake Icing (recipe follows).

title: date and nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, pour boiling water over the walnuts, dates and raisins and let stand until cooled.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: lemon cream cheese rice pie
directions: Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients and add cooled rice.
Pour into heavily buttered glass baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 300 degrees until set.

title: "wangs" buffalo chicken wings
directions: Bake frozen wings on rack in a large pan at 425° for 1 hour.

title: tammie's velveeta  fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese in double boiler or microwave oven. Mix with remaining ingredients.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Chill, then cut.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Line pan with salted chicken.
Sprinkle with rice.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken and rice.
Bake at 375° covered with foil until chicken rice is tender.

title: banana nugget cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg, bananas, oats and chocolate pieces.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a moderately hot 400° oven about 15 minutes, or until cookies are done.
Remove from pan immediately.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: grilled cajun shrimp
directions: Put shrimp on metal skewers.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with seasoning.
Cook on grill for 3 to 5 minutes on each side until done.
Don't overcook.
Serve on rice.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash pumpkin seeds well, and remove any pulp.
Let dry or drain on paper towel.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons butter on top.
Place in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir every 5 minutes to coat seeds with melted butter.
Remove from oven and salt.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Place butter in baking dish and place in preheated moderate oven (375°).
Watch carefully while melting butter.
Dip fish in beaten egg, then in crumbs.
Coat well.
Place each fillet in butter, turning to coat evenly.
Season to taste.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no peek steak
directions: Lay ingredients in bottom of dish.
Put all cream stuff on top of steak.
Put
mushrooms
on last.
Put on top.
Stick in oven at 225° for 4 hours.
Don't peek.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese in microwave. Add peanut butter and microwave for 1 minute. Add vanilla and powdered sugar and stir until smooth. Pour into buttered pan. Chill. Cut into squares.

title: crispy peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in saucepan; remove from heat. Pour in sugar, then crispy rice.
Blend well and chill.
Roll into small size balls.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix. Put in a little cinnamon and nutmeg, if you like it.
Bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain cherry juice into saucepan, reserving cherries.
Add sugar and water; bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over gelatin, mixing well.
Allow to stand until syrupy.
Add pineapple, cherries, nuts and Coke.
Mix well.
Chill until completely set.

title: dijon shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, cook bacon, leaving drippings in pan.
Add butter or margarine to pan and bring to boil.
Add mustard, basil, pepper, onion and crab boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Add shrimp to mixture; stir well and cook 3 minutes.
Pour mixture in casserole dish; cover and cook 20 minutes in oven.
Serve over cooked pasta or rice.

title: savory hamburger supper
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a 3-quart saucepan.
Drain. Return to pan.
Stir in chili powder.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Stir in macaroni, tomatoes and corn.
Simmer uncovered over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in contents of Cheddar cheese mix packet.
Serve immediately.

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Combine yeast and warm water in a large bowl; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add melted shortening (cooled), sugar, salt and nutmeg. Add milk and eggs and stir until well blended.
Gradually add flour, first 1 cup and then the remaining flour, beating until batter is smooth and satiny.
Don't use too much flour; the dough should still be soft.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead a few times until dough is easy to handle.
Let dough rise for about 30 minutes.
Punch down.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Divide each into 6 smaller portions.
Shape each portion into a small round ball.
Place into muffin tins or paper cups. Let rise, covered, for another 50 to 60 minutes or until doubled. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown and light.

title: ranch crackers
directions: Combine dressing mix, dill weed & oil.
Pour over crackers, stir to coat.
Bake at 250° for 15-20 minutes.
Stir gently during baking.

title: it's cheaper fish patties
directions: Drain most of the juice from the mackerel.
Add egg and crushed crackers.
Melt about 1 cup of lard in skillet.
Make mixture into patties and roll in cornmeal.
Fry in moderate heat until browned.

title: old-fashioned chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken, reserving broth in Dutch oven; discard vegetables and bay leaf.
Let chicken cool; skin, bone and cut into bite sized pieces.

title: smoked cheddar muffins
directions: In a medium mixing bowl stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, salt, and red pepper.
In another bowl, beat together eggs, milk, and melted butter.
Add to flour mixture. Add the 1 cup shredded cheese and stir just till batter is smooth (do not overbeat).
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups, filling cups almost full.
Top with desired toppings.
Bake in a 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or till golden brown.
Let cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Remove from muffin cups and serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken stew with dumplings(serves 4)
directions: Bring water to boil in a 6-quart pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add dumplings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon; drain, crumble and set aside.
Mix together the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Add raisins, bacon and onion. Stir all together with broccoli (and cauliflower); marinate for 2 to 4 hours.

title: best-ever cake
directions: Mix everything together and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: ragu and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Heat milk and margarine.
Add cheese. Stir until cheese melts.
Pour over macaroni.
Set aside.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain; return to skillet.
Add Ragu spaghetti sauce; simmer 10 minutes in a greased baking dish.
Put 1/2 of the hamburger and Ragu.
Put 1/2 of macaroni and cheese on top of hamburger.
Layer the other half of hamburger on top of cheese and macaroni.
Add the rest of the macaroni and cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Gradually add sugar to beaten eggs, then add pumpkin.
Add flour, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Pour onto jelly roll pan well greased and floured.
Bake only 15 minutes at 375° .
Sprinkle a dish towel with powdered sugar. Flip hot cake out on towel.
Roll up and let cool.

title: angel gingerbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add hot water and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix on slow speed, scraping bowl often.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 60 minutes or until the center is solid.

title: oven beef burgundy
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole with Kitchen Bouquet.
Mix in cream of rice.
Cut carrots in half crosswise and 1/4 lengthwise.
Mix gently.
Bake in 325° oven for 2 hours.
Stir every 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Mix gelatin with hot water and salt.
Add mayonnaise to a small portion of hot liquid and stir until smooth.
Return to other mixture.
Chill to egg white consistency, then add applesauce, olives and nuts.
Mold, chill and serve on lettuce.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bake a chocolate fudge cake.

title: cole slaw-er-cucumbers
directions: Combine ingredients.
Boil for 1 minute (until sugar is dissolved).
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Can store about 1 month.

title: peanut butter stuffing
directions: Thoroughly
work
together
the first three ingredients with hands.
Add
bread	crumbs	until
mixture	just
sticks together enough
to	handle easily.	Taste for flavor, adding salt
and onion powder if desired.
(It will taste just about the
same when
cooked,
so
taste accordingly.) Stuff turkey about 3/4 full.
This recipe is for a 12 to 15 pound bird.

title: baby spinach salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together. An oil-based dressing seems to set off the spinach; Ranch dressing works well also. Serves 2 to 3.

title: herb french bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix herbs in softened butter and pour over sliced bread.
Sprinkle with cheese and roll bread in foil. Bake until hot.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and mix well. Add milk and vanilla.
Strain mixture as you pour it into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes. Do not overbake or it will get watery.

title: muncho gusto munchies
directions: Line a salad plate with half the lettuce.
Spoon bean dip on lettuce.
Spread half of the sour cream dip over bean dip. Sprinkle with half of the tomato, half of cheese and half of olives.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix until smooth and creamy.
Use as a fruit dip. Strawberries are really good.

title: mock oyster dip
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushroom pieces.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well.
Combine and add mushroom soup.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Combine in chafing dish to serve.
Serves 12.
Freezes beautifully.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 c. nuts to roll cheese ball in. Refrigerate before serving.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Cook until small amount forms hard ball in cold water.
Pour syrup gradually into egg whites and pecans.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Mix in egg and molasses. Add flour, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon and ginger.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 300° until pie is soft in the middle.

title: spice tea mix
directions: Use 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: make ahead vegetable stuffing
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter until tender but not brown.
Add corn, water, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over stuffing mix and toss lightly.
Stir in eggs. Put in a baking dish and pour melted butter over.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Make ahead and refrigerate, if desired.
Very good.

title: apple oatmeal bars
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and brown sugar.
Add oatmeal. Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Place half mixture in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange sliced apples over mixture.
Dot with butter and sprinkle sugar over apples.
Top with remaining mixture.
Bake in 375° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with hard sauce.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well.
Put in crock-pot on low heat for 4 to 9 hours.
Mix well.
A double batch fills a big crock-pot.

title: easy barbecue chicken sandwiches
directions: Spray your crock-pot with nonstick spray.
Place frozen chicken breasts in crock-pot and cover with bottle of barbecue sauce.
Cook on high all day.
Use a whisk and break apart the chicken until shredded.
Serve on buns.
Delicious and easy!

title: broccoli and cheese dip
directions: In a large crock pot, melt butter.
Add flour to make a paste and then add the broccoli, onion, mushrooms, and soup, heating thoroughly.
Add cheese and heat until melted.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Serve with chips.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Pour
undiluted
lemonade into punch bowl or container. Add the ginger ale and ice cubes.
Stir in sherbet.

title: cheesy hors d'oeuvre
directions: Combine cheese, mushrooms, mayonnaise, olives, garlic salt, onion and sausage.
Mix well.
Top each cracker with 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture.
Place on plate and microwave 50 to 60 seconds on High or until cheese melts.
Serves 24 to 30.

title: noodles, sour cream and chives
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender (5 to 7 minutes) and drain.
In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add 2 tablespoons of onions or chives, half of the cheese, sour cream and nutmeg. Toss lightly with noodles.
Place in serving bowl and top with remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with ham, fruit salad, bread and dessert.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: firecracker corn sticks
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until batter is smooth.
Place 2 well-greased cast-iron corn stick pans in a 450° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove pans from oven.
Spoon batter into pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Yields 14 corn sticks.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Continue cutting and mixing until mixture is creamy.
Press into pan and shape.
Bake until light golden brown.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Put in an airtight container and store in a dry place.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix together; spread in cake pan.
Pour taco sauce over.
Sprinkle on onions, lettuce and tomatoes.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Mix rice, peas, carrots and scallions, then add remaining mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: white enchiladas
directions: Cook, cool and cube chicken.
Mix cheeses with soup.
Mix sour cream with peppers.
Fold 3/4 of cheese mixture into sour cream mixture; add chicken.
Soften tortillas in small amount of oil; fill with chicken mixture.
Roll and place in greased baking dish, seam side down.
Top with remaining cheese-soup mixture.
Sprinkle a little more cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 10 minutes more.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 12.

title: pasta all'erbie(italian - area of toscany)
directions: Cooking time is about 15 minutes.
While pasta is cooking, chop herbs finely.
Strain pasta and put in a serving dish and mix in tomatoes.
Pile all mixed herbs on top of pasta.
Heat olive oil until very hot (but not burning).
Pour over herbs (you can hear them sizzling).
Mix all together.
Cut cubes of Mozzarella cheese.
Arrange on top.
Don't forget the salt and pepper!
Buon appetito!

title: old-fashioned soft cookies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk until fluffy.
Mix in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk; then mix in vanilla.
Fold in egg white, beaten stiff. Drop by tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with spatula to 1/2 inch thickness.
Bake until golden brown in 350° oven about 15 minutes.
Yields 18 cookies.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all together by hand and pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool cake before icing.

title: ribbon squares(makes 12 servings)
directions: Dissolve each flavor of Jell-O in separate bowls, using 1 cup of the boiling water for each.

title: pistou(vegetables with basil)
directions: Brown eggplant in a skillet, cook green pepper and onion with garlic, parsley and basil in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes, or until done, stirring occasionally.

title: orange pears
directions: Sift white sugar with cornstarch.
Blend with other ingredients.
Cook in heavy saucepan over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Arrange pear halves in baking dish.
Spoon sauce over pears.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
If fresh pears are used, check for tenderness of pears.
They may need to bake a little longer.

title: scrambled tofu
directions: Place oil in skillet.
Braise celery and onion.
Break tofu into small pieces and add to remaining ingredients, stirring well. Add to skillet and simmer, stirring from time to time until heated through.
Serve in place of scrambled eggs.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Scald milk; reserve 1/3 cup and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt to hot milk; stir well.
Cool, then add eggs and yeast.
Add flour, working in white flour first.
Work well with spoon, but don't knead.
Cover and set aside to rise.
When double in size, punch down, knead and shape into rolls.
Let rise to double in size. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 400° oven.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs and 1 cup milk, then add sugar. Mix well. Add 1 cup of milk and stir. Prepare flour with warm water (approximately 1/2 cup), enough to stir and then add to mixture. Cook mixture either on stove top or in microwave. If microwave is used, stir every 2 minutes until consistency is thick. Remove from heat, adding butter and vanilla. Pour in prepared pie shell. Cover with egg yolks and bake until topping has browned.

title: southern style buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut and blend in shortening to the flour, powder and salt, consistency of coarse meal.
Add milk.
Stir until it leaves sides of bowl. On floured surface, toss until no longer sticky.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add sauce and simmer. Add cottage cheese.
Boil noodles and drain.
Layer sauce, noodles and Mozzarella cheese until used up.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes uncovered.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat and pour in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix in order of listing.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chili with beans
directions: Put ground beef in large saucepan. Add salt, pepper, Accent and onions in 1-inch of water. Boil until meat is done. Add rest of ingredients. Cook about 20 minutes.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Put chicken in Dutch oven.
Cover with seasonings, soup mix, rice, soup and milk.
Cover very tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Do not peek!

title: cream cheese ball
directions: By hand, mix softened cream cheese, onion, green pepper and 1/3 cup pecans.
Add drained pineapple.
Season to taste with Lawry's seasoned salt.
Roll into a ball.
Roll ball in remainder of nuts.

title: bouillon poached fish
directions: In large skillet, or electric skillet, dissolve bouillon with water over medium heat.
Add vegetables, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add fish; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
4 servings.
Only 1 1/2 Weight Watcher Points per 4 oz. serving.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix all together except sour cream.
Pour half into mold until slightly jelled and add layer of sour cream.
Add remaining jello. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered pot.
(I use an electric skillet.)
Cook on medium heat for 45 minutes.
Stir once or twice.
Serve with salad of your choice.

title: fruited pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until
light
and
fluffy.	Add
eggs,
one at a time, beating well after each one.
Combine 1 3/4 cups flour and the baking
powder.
Gradually	add
to
creamed
mixture and beat until
well
blended.
Dredge
lemon rind, candied fruit, raisins, dates
and pecans with remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Stir to coat well.
Stir mixture into batter.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch
tube
pan.
Bake
at
for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until done.
Cool about 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Dust top of cake with powdered sugar.
Garnish with candied cherries and pineapples.
Very good for the holidays.

title: sponge cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes a soft sugar cookie.

title: cherry burst pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in remaining ingredients, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze until firm, 2 to 3 hours.
Serve at room temperature.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in large pot or Dutch oven.
Drain meat mixture if necessary.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas, to meat mixture and heat until cheese melts.
Cut tortillas in quarters.

title: jamy's cookies
directions: Cream butter, eggs, sugar, brown sugar, and vanilla together then add flour, oatmeal, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop tablespoon size cookies on cookie sheet.
Bake cookies at 375 degrees for 6 - 8 minutes (bottoms should be "light brown" - may look a little gooey on top of cookie).

title: hamburger and hominy
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Add hominy, butter or oil, onion, green pepper, salt, black pepper, chili powder, sugar and tomatoes.
Cook until hominy, onion, pepper and tomatoes look well cooked.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and spread on a flat dish.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and olives before serving.
Serve with taco chips.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut up 1 small can pimento. Mix all together and let stand 24 hours.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Top with bacon bits or crushed potato chips (optional).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: methodist punch
directions: Mix well, chill and serve with sherbet.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Then blend in shortening. Make a hole in the center of mixture, drop in the unbeaten eggs and vanilla. Mix together. Pick up dough with your hands and roll into small balls. Mash down with a small glass. Dip glass with sugar and press cookie dough flat. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar when done.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Place corn chips on bottom of dish. Add chicken as second layer.
Mix chilies, onion, salt and pepper. Spread over chicken.
Spread cheese over mixture and cover with sour cream.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet-sour ham rice skillet
directions: Cook ham, onion and green pepper in butter until onion is tender.
Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add liquid, rice, pineapple, brown sugar, vinegar and salt to ham; stir.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Put it in a pot and turn it on.
Let it get hot to where the sugar goes down to the bottom and melts.

title: potato scramble
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain off all but 3 tablespoons fat. Cook and stir potatoes, onion, salt and pepper in fat until browned.
Pour eggs in skillet.
Cook uncovered until eggs are thickened.
Serves 4. (Substitution:
Cooked potatoes is equal to 1 (9-ounce) package of frozen French fried potatoes, diced.)

title: rice krispie delights
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave for 2 minutes.
Mix together.
Spoon out on wax paper by the teaspoonful.
Let harden. Makes about 60.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese bars
directions: Grease
9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice 1 roll of cookie dough and lay in bottom of pan.
Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Pour over cookie dough.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix well and pour enough Italian salad dressing over to suit your taste.
Let set 4 hours or overnight.

title: macaroni cheese bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, drain. Mix all other ingredients together, add macaroni and 1/2 cup cheese. Pour into baking dish and top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake in 400 degree oven for 20-25 minutes. If you like it cheesier, add few slices Velveeta.

title: lite coconut pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Place all ingredients in a large bowl and beat until smooth; batter will be a little lumpy.
Beat by hand.
Pour ingredients into pie plate. Sprinkle top with a little coconut and bake 50 to 55 minutes. Test with knife in center.
When done will come out clean.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
Spread 1/2 cup walnuts evenly on bottom of pan.
Set aside.
In heavy gauge saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt. Bring to full rolling boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butterscotch flavored morsels; stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in orange extract and orange rind.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup walnuts on top. Chill until firm (about 2 hours).

title: angel cake
directions: Sift flour and 1/2 cup sugar 4 times and set aside.
Ina large bowl combine egg whites, cream of tartar, extracts and salt.
Beat on high until mixture stands in high peaks.
Mixture should be moist and glossy.
Add remaining sugar 1/4 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour mixture 1/4 at a time over egg mixture.
Fold this in gently about 15 strokes after each addition.
Spoon batter into a 10-inch ungreased tube pan.
Pan will be very full.
Bake at 375° for 34 to 40 minutes or until top is golden.
Immediately invert cake when cool.
Loosen sides and remove.

title: cinnamon graham sundaes
directions: For each serving, place 2 graham cracker squares on a plate. Top with ice cream and drizzle with honey.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Yields 10 servings.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Then add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir. Then add melted butter.
Divide pecans between two regular pie crusts and pour mixture over.
Pecans will rise to top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Recipe can be halved for one pie.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: You will need three 1 pound coffee cans.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Place almond bark and chocolate chips in glass baking dish or casserole.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes, or until melted. Stir occasionally.
Add peanuts; stir and drop a teaspoonful of mixture onto a wax paper covered cookie sheet.
Let set until firm (1 hour) or place in freezer until cool (5 to 10 minutes). Then place candy in covered tin and keep in refrigerator.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Shape 1/3 cups of mixture into patties.
Heat large nonstick skillet sprayed with cooking spray on medium heat.
Add patties and cook approximately 3 minutes on each side.
(Or, until patties are golden brown on both sides.)
Turn carefully.
Makes 12 salmon patties.

title: layered shrimp appetizer
directions: Place on serving dish, layered in the above order, starting at the top.
Top with chopped tomatoes.
Serve with buttery crackers.

title: lemon-strawberry punch
directions: Dilute lemonade and mix with strawberries and ginger ale. Makes 1 gallon.
Serves 32.

title: cole slaw
directions: * Do not peel apple.

title: tomato and broccoli bake
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water 8 to 10 minutes; drain well. In saucepan, cook onion and garlic in butter or margarine until tender.
Add the tomatoes, parsley, broth, oregano, basil and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling.
Add broccoli; cover, simmer 4 minutes.
Add pasta to tomato mixture.
Turn into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crock-pot vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot all day on low.
Dinner is done when you get home!

title: melt in your mouth turkey
directions: Place turkey in large stock pot (I use a canner).
Place a saucer or small cake pan under turkey.
Cover with water.
Salt to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until just done. Let cool until you can remove from pot.
Place in broiler pan; rub skin with butter or margarine.
Brown in oven.
Use reserved stock for stuffing and gravy.

title: onion pie
directions: Place cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter in pie plate. Mix and press into crust.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water after it is almost jelled.
Fold in crushed pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Add chopped walnuts.
Chill.

title: roman egg and cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, bring broth and water to a boil.
Add pasta and cook until pasta is tender.
Reduce heat.
Stir in cheese, parsley and nutmeg. Slowly pour egg in simmering broth.
Stir.
Serve immediately.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix well.
Grease bread pan.
Pour into bread pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: shake and bake potatoes
directions: Melt margarine	in large baking pan.
Cut potato wedges to approximately 1/2-inch thickness.
Place wedges in bag with Shake 'n Bake seasoning.	Shake until all potatoes are coated. Place in melted margarine.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: hash browns and meat pie
directions: Prepare pie crust mix.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Combine ground beef, milk, soup mix, pepper and allspice.
Lightly pat into pastry shell.
Top with thawed hash browns.
Adjust top crust; seal and flute edges.
Cut a few slits in the top crust.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup tomato sauce.
In large bowl, thoroughly combine beef, turkey or chicken, bread crumbs, Egg Beaters, onion, garlic, oregano and remaining tomato sauce.
Shape into 9 x 4-inch loaf.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spread reserved tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes more or until internal temperature reaches 165°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: gil's bloody mary
directions: Place vodka and ice in large goblet. Add other ingredients. Stir don't shake. Garnish with slice of lime and serve with nice crisp piece of celery.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Place
all ingredients in the blender or food processor and blend
until smooth.
Leftovers will keep for a day or can be frozen
for pops. Yields 3 cups.
Contains 1 gram fat and 3 grams fiber per cup.

title: muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 425°. Makes 10 servings.

title: yum yum
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1 c. sugar.
Whip dream whip according to directions.
Mix in with cream cheese mixture.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Place layer of cracker crumbs in bottom of 9x13 dish.
Place layer of cream cheese mix, layer of pie filling, another layer of cream cheese, sprinkle top with cracker crumbs and chill.

title: nontraditional sweet freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt in large bowl; cover with plastic wrap. Set bowl on counter for 2 hours. Pour into colander and drain water from mixture. Combine the sugar and vinegar. Stir well and pour over cucumbers. Pack into freezer containers or bags. Freeze immediately. Pickles are ready to eat in 3 or 4 days. They will keep in freezer for up to a year.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Cream butter or margarine and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in mini chips; spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely; cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: bread dip
directions: Cut out the center of a round loaf to make a bowl.
Cut up the bread you removed into square or rectangular pieces to use for dipping.
You can put all the bread back into a plastic bag to keep fresh until ready to serve.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Fold next 3 ingredients together and spread over baked pretzel mixture. Set aside.
Mix jello, water and berries together.
Refrigerate until chilled and pour over Cool Whip mixture.
Sprinkle top with crushed pretzels before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: delicate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except egg whites and 1 cup sugar.
Put in 2 layer pans.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1 cup granulated sugar.
Spread over batter in layer pans (2) and bake about 1 hour slowly at 275°.
Be sure to first grease and flour cake pans.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: layered salad
directions: Arrange in layers the lettuce, celery, green peppers, onion, green peas and Cheddar cheese (this is optional or light cheese may be used).
Top with bacon bits.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix. Spread on a plate or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chop the vegetables and cheese and sprinkle over the top.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add vanilla, eggs and baking powder.
Add cracker crumbs and milk alternately.
Mix well.
Add pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Mix well and bake in 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 70 minutes until done.

title: carrot salad
directions: Grate carrots.
Mix in salad bowl, all ingredients. Refrigerate.
Ready to serve.

title: dairy orange salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello. Add the marshmallows and sit until jello is dissolved. Defrost the orange juice and stir in 1/2 cup sugar. Add to jello mixture. Cream the cream cheese and add the crushed pineapple to the cheese. Add this to the jello mixture. Next, add the cottage cheese, bananas and orange sections and stir until well mixed. Fold in the whipped cream. Pour in a large container and place in refrigerator about 3 hours.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Get out your monster pot.
Cook rice according to package directions; set aside.
Saute onions and celery in oil in a large skillet until crisp-tender.
Stir in garlic, sausage (1/4-inch slices) and ham.
Cook an additional 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in cooked rice.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Yields 15 servings.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Clean jalapeno peppers; remove seeds and drain.
Mix sausage, Cheddar cheese and Bisquick.
Stuff peppers with small sliver of Monterey Jack cheese; wrap with sausage mix.
Dip in beaten eggs; roll in Shake 'n Bake mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes. Can be frozen and used later, also.
Yields 25 peppers. Delicious.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and salt and continue beating for a while.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla; fold in nuts and chips.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet covered with ungreased foil.
Put in oven.
Immediately cut off heat.
Leave overnight.
Do not open oven!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the last 4 ingredients.
Pour over the broccoli mixture and combine before serving.

title: tuna swiss pie
directions: Pierce pastry thoroughly with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove.
In
a large bowl, toss tuna, cheese and onion. Spoon
into
pastry.
In
bowl stir remaining ingredients.
Slowly pour
over
tuna
mixture.
Bake
50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: ugly black cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 9 X 13 pan. Batter will be runny. Bake at 300 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix next 5 ingredients. Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix milk, butter and cheese in microwave; saute onions, add to	potatoes
and
pour
cheese mixture over potatoes and onions. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
You might use O'Brien potatoes and leave out the onions.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 45 minutes.
Divide into 2 balls and shape. Chill overnight before using.

title: holiday chocolate mousse
directions: In a double boiler or heavy saucepan, heat chocolate Riesen caramels and heavy cream over low heat; stir until smooth.
Stir in rum extract.
Pour chocolate mixture into mixing bowl.
Cool 3 to 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and spoon into small dessert cups. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: quick stir-fry meal
directions: In frypan or wok, add water, onion (separated into rings), broccoli, cauliflower and green peppers.
Let simmer with lid on until tender.
Cut steak (chicken, pork etc.) into bite size pieces and add to vegetables.
Leave pan covered and cook until meat is done.

title: hungarian beef and noodles
directions: Cook meat in a large skillet, breaking it up with a spoon as it cooks, until no pink remains.
Stir in onion; cook until tender, about 3 minutes.
Blend in broth, mustard and tomato paste.
Bring to boiling; lower heat and cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream very slowly to prevent curdling. Heat gently, but do not allow to boil.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: banana pudding
directions: First layer your bananas and wafers in a glass dish.
In medium saucepan, mix flour and sugar together. Then add eggs and mix well.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Cook until mixture thickens and pour over wafers and bananas.

title: macaroni cheese(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook macaroni.
Cut up tomatoes and add macaroni (well drained).
Stir.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Use hamburger (uncooked) or ham.
Layer macaroni, meat, macaroni, meat and macaroni.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: coconut condensed milk pie
directions: Mix eggs
and
sugar; beat in flour; add other ingredients. Melt
margarine; beat well.
Put into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for
to
40 minutes or until set and golden brown; cool.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix with hands and pat in a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake until brown.

title: red corn cob jelly
directions: Wash corn cobs and break into small pieces.
Cook in 8 cups water.
Bring to a boil and cook for 30 minutes, boiling slowly, then strain, put in a pan and add Sure-Jell.
Bring to a boil and boil hard for 1 1/2 minutes, then add sugar and boil for 1 1/2 minutes again or until jelly sheets from spoon.
Pour into jars.

title: fool proof chocolate icing
directions: Combine all ingredients except cream. Mix on low speed adding cream gradually, keeping at spreading consistency.

title: icebox cucumber pickles
directions: Bring all ingredients (except cucumbers) to boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool, pour over sliced cucumbers and put in refrigerator.
The thinner sliced, the better!

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Drain liquid from clams; add water to make 2 cups liquid.
Add potatoes and onion to liquid; cook until tender.
Fry bacon; cut in small pieces.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients to vegetables; heat slowly for 10 minutes but do not boil.
Yields 6 servings.

title: honey glazed baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and drain.
Shake in a paper bag in a mixture of flour, salt and pepper to coat well.
Melt 4 tablespoons margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Roll chicken pieces, one at a time in melted butter to coat all over. Place, skin side down, in a single layer in the baking dish.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Melt remaining 4 tablespoons margarine in a small saucepan; stir in honey, lemon juice and soy sauce until well mixed.
Turn chicken and pour honey mixture over breasts.
Bake, basting several times with syrup and drippings in pan.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until tender and richly glazed.
This is delicious!
Cover baking dish with foil to bake.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in rectangular pan in oven. Mix Bisquick, paprika and salt. Coat chicken.
Place skin sides down in pan. Bake 35 minutes. Turn and bake another 15 minutes or until done.
This recipe works well with pork chops, too.

title: mustard sauce(microwave)
directions: Mix together and heat on 40% power for 2 to 3 minutes.
Great served with ham or corned beef and cabbage.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain and dry fruit.
Arrange in a flat casserole.
Melt butter and mix with brown sugar and curry powder.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Allow to cool for one hour before serving.

title: gumbo(quick, easy, delicious!)
directions: Boil chicken, debone and chop. Add enough water to broth to make 6 cups. Brown flour in shortening (or oleo) and make a dark brown roux.

Add chopped onion, bell pepper, celery, salt and pepper. Cook until tender. Stir into boiling broth. Add chicken, sausage and okra. Cook until tender. Add bay leaf. Simmer 30 minutes. Add shrimp and cook a few minutes (10 to 15) longer until shrimp are pink and tender. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Remove bay leaf and serve over hot cooked rice. Delicious served with a hot, buttered baked sweet potato, salad and French bread.

title: coconut-sour cream cake
directions: Bake cake by directions in two layers.
Let cool. Mix together sour cream, coconut and sugar and set aside.
Slice each cake layer into two layers, making a total of 4 thin layers.
Put about 1/2 to 3/4 cup of mixture between your cake layers, stacking one on top of another.
Mix Cool Whip with remaining mixture which should be about 1 1/2 cups or so and frost the cake.
Cover cake with Saran Wrap carefully and refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: yellow cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, add sugar gradually until light and fluffy.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Bake 30-35 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Melt and mix butter with onions until translucent.
Mix in beans and stir until all is well blended.
Cook on low heat, stirring occasionally and add your cheese and stir until all cheese melts.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together Crisco, eggs and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and sugar.
Mix Crisco mixture and flour mixture together.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: mammy's pancakes and waffles
directions: Whip egg whites first.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and add egg whites.

title: hermits
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Then beat in the egg and sour cream.
Add flour and spices and beat until smooth.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Drop the batter from a teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix well the eggs, fruit, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Add dry coconut flakes on top of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon turbot casserole
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Slowly add eggs and lemon juice.
Season to taste.
Layer sauce with cooked macaroni on bottom, then salmon, then sauce in alternate layers in a greased casserole. Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheesy pasta swirls(ready to bake in 15 minutes)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Spray 8 x 12-inch baking dish with Pam. Combine vegetables, Mozzarella, Provolone and 1/2 can onions. Twirl a few strands of hot fettucine around fork to form a swirl. Remove from fork and stand upright on top of vegetable mixture. Form 5 more swirls.
In medium bowl, stir together soup, milk and garlic powder.
Pour over swirls.
Bake, loosely covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top pasta with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle onion around swirls.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes until brown.

title: grape jelly
directions: Add exact amount of sugar to the juice and mix well. Place over high heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Skim off foam with metal spoon and pour jelly into glasses.
Seal with paraffin.

title: blueberry tea bread
directions: About 3 hours before serving:

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Put meat in bottom of casserole.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Layer on top of meat.
Pour can of soup on top of potatoes and cover with foil.
Cook for about an hour or until potatoes are soft.
Cook at 350°.
Right before you are ready to take out of oven, put can of onions on top and brown.
Feeds 2 to 4.

title: cold curried pea soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a saucepan. Add 1 cup chicken broth. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Cool slightly.
Spoon mixture into container of an electric blender. Add remaining broth. Process until smooth.
Return vegetable mixture to saucepan. Stir in milk and cream.
Chill.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple well.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: diabetic applesauce bread
