directions: Sift flour, spices, salt and soda together.
Add Equal, applesauce, egg, oil, raisins, nuts and apple.
Mix well.
Pour into a medium loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: basic brunswick stew
directions: Simmer chicken in a large pot with water and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt until tender.
Drain broth and save.
Remove chicken bones and skin.
Cut chicken into small bite size pieces.
Skim fat from broth.
Return broth to pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce broth to 2 cups, but save remainder.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup; microwave 4 minutes on High.
Stir in peanuts; microwave 4 minutes on High.
Add oleo and vanilla; stir.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Remove.
Stir in soda.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: lo-cal cream pie
directions: Put undrained pineapple in bowl; add vanilla pudding and stir. Add light sour cream and stir.
Stir well and put in pie crust.

title: mother's lifetime recipe
directions: Take 1 large field, half a dozen children, 2 or 3 small dogs, a pinch of brook and some pebbles.
Mix the children and dogs well together.
Put them on a field, stirring constantly.
Pour the book over the pebbles.
Sprinkle the field with flowers; spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and baking soda.
In a separate bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in the egg and vanilla.
Drain the pineapple reserving the liquid.
Add enough water to the liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir into the egg mixture.
Add to the flour mixture; stir until just moist.
Fold in the drained pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Fill greased muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into salmon mixture.
Bake.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small, bite size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 450°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hares in their stew.

title: french toast, honey style
directions: Beat eggs with a whisk.
Add the milk, honey and salt.
Melt butter.
Dip the bread into the mixture.
Cook until golden brown. Top with syrup.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm. Decorate top with grated unsweetened chocolate, if desired.

title: quick potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients with thawed potatoes in a large Pyrex baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Stir every 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chicken divan
directions: Note:
Chicken does not have to be cut into pieces.

title: coconut mounds cake
directions: Fix devil's food cake as directed.
Cool.
In saucepan melt sugar, milk and marshmallows.
Do not boil.
Stir in coconut.
Mix together oleo, cocoa, confectioners sugar and 7 tablespoons milk. After cake cools, slice each layer and alternate coconut and chocolate icing, with chocolate icing on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Tastes like a Mounds candy bar.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Chop the artichokes and add the other 2 ingredients. Stir together and place in a small baking dish and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until slightly brown on top and bubbly. Serve with crispy crackers, such as Triscuits, Wheat Thins, etc.

title: sloppy joes with rice
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in large skillet on medium heat; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Bring water and salt to boil in medium saucepan.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serve meat mixture over rice. Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: Place potatoes in soup pot; sprinkle with salt and cover with water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Meanwhile, in skillet, cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in corn and cooked bacon; heat through.
Drain potatoes; add milk.
Heat through.
Stir in corn and cheese.
Serve.

title: red punch
directions: Mix everything except ginger ale and chill.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.

title: sausage stars
directions: Take 2 heaping cups of patience, 1 heartful of love, 2 handfuls of generosity, a dash of laughter and 1 headful of understanding. Sprinkle generously with kindness. Add plenty of faith and mix well. Spread over the period of a lifetime and serve everybody you meet.

title: rotkohl (red cabbage)
directions: Grate cabbage coarsely.
Place in bowl.
Add vinegar.
Let sit until cabbage turns bright red.

title: overnight scalloped chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Add meat, macaroni and eggs. Stir in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Cover.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Toss crumbs with remaining melted butter.
Put on top of casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Roll into balls and set in fridge until chilled.
Dip into melted chocolate and set onto wax paper until cool.

title: rita's sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread generously on bread and top with second slice.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare and cut up apples;
arrange
in pie plate.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon;
sprinkle over apples.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and flour, cut
in
butter
until
crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in hot oven
for 40 minutes or until done.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Pat out crescent rolls into a 17 x 11-inch cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown; cool.
Soften cream cheese with mixer.
Add Ranch dressing.
Spread onto baked crust.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Add veggies, arranging colors attractively.
Cut and serve.

title: sugar-free banana muffins
directions: Put eggs and banana and soda into blender high speed until smooth, few minutes.
Empty into medium mixing bowl.
Work in each remaining ingredient, stirring only until all dry particles are completely dissolved.
Divide batter equally between 12 paper lined cupcake or muffin wells.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: parmesan biscuits
directions: Melt
butter in 8-inch round cake pan.	Add seasonings, except sesame
seed and mix with butter.
Roll biscuits in mix and arrange
in spoke-wheel fashion.
Sprinkle sesame seed on top. Bake according to package directions.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 pan. Add pecans and coconut, then toast at 350°. While that mixture cools, combine sweetened condensed milk and cream cheese, then fold in Cool Whip. Pour this mixture into pie shells. Sprinkle coconut mixture on top and drizzle with caramel ice cream topping. Freeze pies until ready to serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles; put them in a deep baking dish.
Mix tuna, soup, milk and peas.
Mix well; add crazy salt and mix again.
Cut butter into little squares.
Mix soup mixture and noodles together.
Put squares of butter over the top and cover.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, covered, stirring once or twice.
When done, sprinkle chips over top and serve.
Grated cheese is good on the top as well.

title: raspberry jello pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch and cook (about 5 to 6 minutes) until thick and clear.
Add small package jello.
Stir in lemon juice.
Cool in fridge; when cool, add raspberries and cool again.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with whipped cream (about 1 pint) and garnish with a few berries.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Tenderize pork chops.
Prepare stuffing, make a little moister than normal.
Place pork chops in baking dish.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Sprinkle with paprika and sliced mushrooms.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Can freeze and reheat in microwave.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Scald oatmeal in water; let stand 20 minutes.
Mix
the sugars and shortening in separate bowl.
Stir in eggs.
Sift together the salt, flour, soda and cinnamon. Add sugar and egg mixture to dry ingredients, then add oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bacon chive corn muffins
directions: Prepare muffin mix according to package directions.
Fold in chives, pepper and bacon.
Turn into 12 greased 2 3/4-inch muffin pans and bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes or until done.
Serve hot.
Makes 12.

title: old fashioned soft pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Cream butter and sugar, add pumpkin, egg and vanilla, beat until light and creamy. Add dry ingredients, mix well. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 5-6 dozen.

title: strawberry "biscuit"
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Have oleo cold; cut into small pieces.
Mix with flour mixture.
Pour milk over flour mixture and mix quickly.
Make into medium-size biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
This biscuit is really good as a bread, also.

title: the ultimate rice krispie treat
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a large saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add Rice Krispies and stir to coat.
Press mixture into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together in small saucepan, then spread over the Rice Krispies.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: oriental dinner
directions: Cut up chicken breasts and pork; fry in large frypan.
When brown appears on bottom of pan, add chicken broth, celery, green beans, onion, green pepper, soy sauce and brown sugar.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Thicken slightly with cornstarch.
Serve over hot rice or crisp noodles.

title: pizza mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Spread on slices of French bread and place under broiler until mixture bubbles.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Put butter, syrup and sugar into medium size pan.
On medium high, let come to a rolling boil.
Take off heat and add peanut butter; mix well.
Add corn flakes.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Arrange wings into baking pan.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour over wings coating well.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 4-6 people.

title: kim's caribbean chicken salad
directions: Grill chicken and dice. Mix all ingredients in large bowl, using Swiss cheese as a topping.

title: spicy raisin bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine cake mix (dry), water, eggs, butter, brown sugar and spices in mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
While warm, spread with lemon glaze.

title: maw maw's chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not add water to chicken soup.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° until desired thickness.

title: granny's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter together. Add eggs, beating well after each addition. Add flavorings, then add flour to make a stiff dough. Roll dough thin. Cut with a big biscuit cutter. Bake cookies at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: barbecue bean casserole
directions: Fry sausage with celery and onion; drain off fat.
Add all beans to sausage mixture; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon and mix well.
Put in 3-quart casserole dish; top with bacon and bake, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: sheepherder's bread
directions: Combine water, butter, sugar and salt.
Stir until butter melts.
Cool to 110°.
Stir in yeast.
Set until bubbly (15 minutes) in warm place.
Beat in 5 cups of the flour to make a thick batter.
Stir in 3 1/2 cups flour to make stiff dough. Knead until smooth and satiny, 10 to 20 minutes.
Put in greased bowl until doubled (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and knead to form a smooth ball.
Cover inside of Dutch oven with foil.
Grease it and the lid.
Place dough in pot and cover.
Let rise 1 hour until lid rises 1/2 inch.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 12 minutes.
Remove lid and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Sounds hollow.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute butter, shrimp and onion.
Saute for 3 to 5 minutes on medium heat.
Shrimp should turn white.
Sprinkle in flour and add sour cream; mix well.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: wild rice
directions: Saute first 7 ingredients.
Add last 2 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: hot tuna or ham sandwich
directions: Let the mistress of the house take 2 pounds of the very best self-control, 1 1/2 pounds of justice, 1 pound of consideration, 5 pounds of patience and 1 pound of discipline.
Let this be sweetened with charity.
Let it simmer well.
Let it be taken daily and be kept always on hand.
The domestic wheels will run quite smoothly.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until tender at 375°. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: halloween chiller punch
directions: Dissolve drink mix, sugar, water, orange juice and chill.

title: cinnamon-raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all dry ingredients and mix in large bowl.
In a small bowl, beat egg, milk and oil.
Add this mixture and raisins to dry ingredients; mix well.
Grease muffin pan and fill the cups half full of the mixture.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook beef and onions; drain. Stir in salt. Spread in 9-inch pie plate. Cover with cheese. Mix milk, Bisquick and eggs well; pour over beef and cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°. Serve hot.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a cookie sheet with vegetable oil spray.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the margarine and sugars.
Stir in egg.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; beat.
In a medium bowl, sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to margarine mixture and mix well.
Form dough into 1 1/2-inch balls and place 3-inches apart on prepared cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake 15 minutes or until done.
Allow cookies to cool 2 to 3 minutes on cookie sheet before transferring to cooling rack.

title: little crabmeat casseroles
directions: Make a cream sauce out of butter, flour and milk.
When it is thick, add seasonings.
Gradually stir in egg yolks, crab meat and mushrooms.
Then pour it into individual ramekins.
Put buttered crumbs on top.
Then Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13 dish. Break chicken in pieces and place in dish. Mix together soup and sour cream. (Add little broth to keep from getting too dry.) Spread over chicken. Spread cracker crumbs over all. Pour margarine over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve hot.

title: psuedo key lime pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip first.
Then add the frozen limeade. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze or refrigerate.

title: fried macaroni
directions: Cook desired amount of macaroni according to package directions.
Drain water.
Scramble desired amount of eggs in a bowl.
Put macaroni in a skillet with bacon drippings and add eggs.
Fry mixture until eggs are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender; mix well.
Use in all recipes that call for Eagle Brand milk.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Put together in layers.
Dip with tortilla chips.
Delicious! Serves 24.

title: ambrosia potato bake
directions: Alternate lemon, orange and sweet potato slices in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine crushed pineapple, brown sugar, butter and salt; pour over potatoes and fruit.
Sprinkle coconut over top; garnish with cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate; mix until blended.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until batter is smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 (8 or 9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, milk and sugar until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on crust.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl of mixer.
Mix for 15 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: mom's rice pilaf
directions: *Stock, broth or water with 1 tablespoon tamari soy sauce or combination of water with cooking wine.

title: lasagna pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook ground beef over medium heat, stirring until crumbled and brown. Drain.
Stir in oregano, basil, tomato paste and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan in pie plate.
Spoon beef mixture over top.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth (15 seconds in blender) or 1 minute with hand mixer. Pour over meat in pie plate.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or knife test comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cool 5 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: melon-liquor-coconut cake
directions: In a large bowl, place all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in pan, then turn onto wire rack and cool completely.

title: italian bread me-o-latie
directions: Rub some cooking oil on counter. Roll out bread dough.
Layer ingredients, Italian sausages, cheese, seasonings.
Roll up like jelly roll and seal.
Bake until golden brown in a 325° oven, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes.
This appetizer goes well.
I make 2 loaves.

title: ruth's mustard
directions: Mix vinegar and mustard and allow to stand overnight.
In the morning, add eggs and sugar.
Cook in double boiler for 20 minutes or until it thickens.
Refrigerate.
Delicious served with raw veggies, ham or cheese.

title: lollipops
directions: Using a wooden spoon, stir first 3 ingredients in saucepan over low heat until dissolved.
Increase to high heat, bring to boil without stirring and cook for 15 to 20 minutes, until 300° or hard ball stage.
Blend in flavoring and coloring.
Slowly pour free shapes and press on sticks.

title: lemon cake custard
directions: Add sugar, flour and
salt together.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend well.
Pour into unbaked single pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: ham roll
directions: Mix together everything but nuts.
Refrigerate until chilled. Form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: spiced tea
directions: Heat water to boiling and add tea bags and heat until steepen. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour.
Serves 25.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs with sugar.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix all together until mix is mixed together.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese-bean pie
directions: Mix Bisquick, water and beans together; pat into a pie plate to make shell (lightly greased pie plate).
Brown hamburger and onions together; drain grease and put hamburger into pie shell. Pour salsa over top of hamburger and then spread grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with sliced avocado and sour cream.

title: plantation okra
directions: Coarsely chop tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients in a heavy skillet and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until okra is tender.
Yields 6 servings.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Add sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add grated zucchini, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder and flour.
Mix well.
Add (optional) nuts, raisins, dates and coconut, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar. Make a paste of the cocoa and part of the food coloring. Add this and the rest of the food coloring to the creamed mixture. Sift flour and salt and add alternately to the mixture with buttermilk. Add vinegar, soda and vanilla to the batter, mixing well. Bake in 3 - 8 inch greased cake pans. Cool and frost between layers and on top and sides with frosting. Bake at 350 degree for 30 minutes.

title: pamela's sand tarts
directions: Sift
dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream butter and add sugar gradually; add orange rind and eggs.
With wooden spoon, slowly add dry ingredients.
Chill for two hours or overnight. Roll very thin.
Cut
with cookie cutters.
Paint each cookie with egg white.
Sprinkle with fancy sugars or cinnamon sugar. Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onions and bell pepper in cooking oil for 15 minutes on medium-low heat.
Place half of grated cheese in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with saute and pepper.
Add remaining cheese on top of onions and pepper.
Combine heavy cream (unwhipped), eggs, pimento and salt to make a sauce.
Pour sauce over cheese and onions.
Sprinkle paprika as a garnish.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes, lower heat to 325° and bake 25 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Cook rice per package instructions.
Saute onion and pepper in half stick of margarine about 5 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, parsley, thyme and crawfish.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add mushroom soup to rice and mix well.
Add crawfish tails, pepper, onion and tomatoes to rice.
Mix well.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and turn rice mixture into baking dish.
Spread with sour cream.
Bake at 350° until bubbles, about 25 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter sunday sauce
directions: Time:
about 10 minutes before serving or early in day. Yield:
about 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Mix well.
Roll out into strips and drop into boiling broth with chicken (with bones removed); salt and pepper broth to taste before adding dumplings.

title: knetilling
directions: Thicken flour with egg and water.
Rub between hands into soup and cook.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add frozen strawberries.
Let cool until syrupy.
Tear cake into two pieces in a 9 x 13 pan.
Pour strawberry mixture over cake.
Put whipped topping on top and refrigerate.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and dissolve.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water to pineapple mixture.
Stir, pour into dish and chill until partially set. Combine cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.
Stir into jello mixture. Chill until firm.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Blend ingredients in microwave or double boiler.

title: tiny fudge tarts
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Measure flour by sifting.
Mix flour and salt; cut in butter.
Sprinkle with water and vanilla; mix well with fork.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate while preparing chocolate.
Melt chocolate bar in double boiler over low heat.
Add paraffin and stir until completely melted.
With toothpick, dip each peanut butter ball in chocolate.
Put on waxed paper to set up.
Depending on the type of chocolate you use, you may need to adjust the amount of paraffin.
When the bonbons are set up, they should have a glossy appearance to them.
These taste very much like Reese's candy.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend peanut butter and butter together.
Stir in confectioners sugar and mix until stiff and mixture pulls away from bowl.
Place into buttered pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Do not toss.
Let all ingredients grow together.

title: baked broccoli casserole
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until spears are almost tender, 10 to 12 minutes.
Place drained broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Beat soup and milk with hand beater until smooth. Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Combine dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: denver potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 inch pie pan.
Mix eggs, onion powder, thyme, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add potatoes, cheese, ham and green pepper.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes; garnish with tomato slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: weber ribs
directions: Soak charcoal for 15 minutes before lighting.
Separate coals into 2 sections (circular cooking).
Light coals and let them get hot.
Sprinkle pepper, seasoning salt, paprika and garlic salt all over the ribs and rub in.
Place ribs on the edge of rack.
Cover and let cook until all ribs are dark brown (approximately 1 1/2 hours).

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream sugar and margarine.
Beat in eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, mixin until just blended.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes (maybe more).
While slightly warm, frost with icing.

title: mexican salad ole
directions: Prepare avocado dressing; cover and refrigerate.
In a 1-quart glass measure or casserole, combine ground beef and sausage.
With a wooden spoon, crumble meat.
Cook in the microwave oven on 70% power, covered with waxed paper, for 6 to 8 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Stir once or twice during cooking, crumbling the meat as you stir.
Drain well.
Set aside while you combine the remaining ingredients for the salad.

title: italian sour cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
In small bowl, beat 2 egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add brown sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in coconut and 1/2 cup ground pecans.
Spread meringue on bottom and up sides of pan to within 1 inch of top.
Blend cake mix, sour cream, Amaretto, 1/2 cup water, eggs and 2 egg yolks at low speed until moistened. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes. Cool completely.
Blend powdered sugar, cocoa, Amaretto, butter, corn syrup and water until smooth.
Spoon over top of cake. Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons ground pecans.
Garnish with cherries.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in a saucepan. Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions 1/8-inch thick.
Saute in butter over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add seasonings up to and including flour.
Mix well, add broth and wine.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add Kitchen Bouquet for coloring if desired.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, brown bread and heat soup.
Layer bread, soup, cheese and broil until cheese melts.

title: crustless pizza
directions: Blend turkey and bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, then bake this long enough to melt cheese.

title: pecan cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.

title: crunch top pumpkin pie
directions: Spread coconut for crust in a 9-inch glass pie plate. Microwave at High 2 minutes.
Microwave 2 tablespoons butter in a small glass custard cup at High 1 minute.
Mix melted butter into coconut.
Spread crust evenly in pie plate.
Microwave at High 2 minutes.
Microwave cream cheese in a 2 1/2-quart glass mixing bowl at High 1/2 to 1 minute.
Add pumpkin, egg, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into coconut crust. Microwave 4 tablespoons butter in a small glass mixing bowl at High, 1/2 to 1 minute.
Stir in pecans, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle topping over pumpkin filling. Microwave at High, 4 to 5 minutes.
Chill before serving.
Yield: one 9-inch pie.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix well and drop in muffin pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute meat and onions in margarine. Add soup, milk, pimento, marjoram, salt and pepper. Cook spaghetti in boiling water; drain. Put in a butter 9 x 13 pan. Pour sauce over. Top with cheeses. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: linguine with shrimp
directions: Saute garlic in 2 teaspoons of olive oil.
Add tomatoes, basil and salt.
Cook over medium heat for about 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook over low heat.
Heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over cooked linguine.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Melt margarine, then add ground beef and brown well.
Add next 5 ingredients and saute in ground meat until soft.
Then add salt, pepper, chili powder and sugar.
Stir well and add tomatoes, corn, beans, potatoes and water.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, until tender.
Serve alone or over rice.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together. Top with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: braunschweiger dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with crackers and sesame seed breadsticks.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Can be made a day ahead for convenience.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the onions and celery until cooked. Add the meat and brown. Place noodles in casserole, add the meat mixture and top with the soups. Bake in 325° oven 1 hour. Serves 6 people.

title: black forest cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Combine pudding, sugar and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread frosting mixture on cake and top with cherries.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave sugar and syrup on high power for 4 minutes. Add peanuts.
Microwave at full power again for 4 minutes. Stir in butter and vanilla. Microwave 1 minute on high. Beat in
baking soda and spread quickly on cookie sheet.
When hardened, break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: angel food cake
directions: Measure sifted flour.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift 4 times. Combine egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and flavoring.
Beat at high speed until soft peaks form.
Sprinkle in rest of sugar, 2 tablespoons at the time, until all is added.
Sift in flour mixture and fold in with large spoon.
Bake in an ungreased tube pan at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze in muffin tins.
Pop out of muffin tins to serve or drop in freezer bags for later.

title: meximelt casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck. Add taco seasoning and garlic salt.

title: sausage hors d'oeuvres
directions: Clean fresh mushrooms.
Carefully snap stem from mushroom cap. Cut stems in small pieces and place in pan of melted butter.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together baking soda, baking powder and salt; mix well. Add oats, bran flakes, chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded 1/8 cup measure onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350°
until edges brown and centers look chewy.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes with sugar, eggs, milk, 1/2 cup butter, coconut, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan or casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, rest of butter and nuts. Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick chicken tetrazzini
directions: In electric skillet, brown chicken pieces in melted butter. Drain excess fat.
Blend cream of mushroom soup with one canful of milk and add to chicken in skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes (soup will thicken).
Gently boil pasta according to package directions.
Five minutes before serving, blend sour cream with sauce in skillet.
Add cooked pasta; gently stir and heat through.
Sprinkle with Parmesan if desired.
Serves 4.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix together and form desired size meat balls.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix in mixer or with fork, not in a blender.
Chill well before serving.

title: smoked sausage soup
directions: Thinly slice turkey smoked sausage, carrots and cabbage. Combine with remaining ingredients in Dutch oven or soup pot. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Makes six 2-cup servings.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Mix all together; chill until ingredients are blended.
(Can use any other vegetables or combination you prefer.)

title: hot apples
directions: Melt margarine	in
pan.
Stir in brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add
apples,
stirring
to
coat with seasonings. Cover and cook
minutes.
Remove cover and add lemon juice. Cook 5 minutes longer or until tender.
Serve warm.

title: waffles
directions: Melt butter; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together and add melted butter after it is cooled.
Ladle into waffle iron sprayed with cooking spray.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Spoon out avocados and mash in a medium bowl.
Add salt, lemon juice, onion and tomato.
Chill.

title: yum yum balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except paraffin wax and chocolate chips, and roll into balls.
Melt paraffin wax with chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate with toothpick and put on wax paper until firm or ready to eat.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack tightly in quart jar.
To each jar, add remaining ingredients (except sugar).
Fill jar with cold water.
Seal tightly (it will not spoil).
Let set 6 months or more.
Rinse and cut in slices.
Add sugar to each quart; stir to dissolve.
I use a Foley utensil.
This makes its own juice.
Let set on counter a couple days, then refrigerate.
Can be used in a couple days.

title: mediterranean salad
directions: Crumble cheese into salad bowl. Add cucumbers, tomatoes and olives.
In small jar with tight fitting lid, combine olive oil, vinegar, green onions, oregano, parsley, basil, thyme leaves and pepper. Shake until well blended.
Pour over cheese and vegetables.
Toss gently. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: chilled antipasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Toss to combine and coat ingredients with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: cheese-olive balls
directions: Blend cheese and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add sauces and mix well.
Stir in flour.
Shape dough around olives, using teaspoon.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 1 minute in blender or 2 minutes with hand mixer.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55minutes.
